1
00:00:07,099 --> 00:00:09,969
[After checking out of the place
hooked up through a friend in Namwon]

2
00:00:09,969 --> 00:00:11,707
- Thanks for letting us stay.
- Thanks for having us.

3
00:00:11,707 --> 00:00:13,593
[After expressing their gratitude]
Thank you so much.

4
00:00:13,593 --> 00:00:15,975
[Second]
Time to draw for the benefit.

5
00:00:15,975 --> 00:00:19,145
[Wins a phone twice in a row]

6
00:00:19,145 --> 00:00:20,847
Oh no.

7
00:00:20,847 --> 00:00:22,927
Honestly, I really don't need
a phone right now.

8
00:00:22,927 --> 00:00:26,385
- Guess we should head out.
- Right, let's make our way to Namwon Station.

9
00:00:26,385 --> 00:00:28,560
[Third destination: Boseong]

10
00:00:28,560 --> 00:00:30,488
[In this cute, charming little town]
Why is everything here so adorable?

11
00:00:30,488 --> 00:00:32,527
- This town is seriously cute.
- Right?

12
00:00:32,527 --> 00:00:33,993
We came here to have fun.

13
00:00:33,993 --> 00:00:35,228
[Hehehehe]

14
00:00:35,228 --> 00:00:36,460
[Met some even cuter elders too]

15
00:00:36,460 --> 00:00:37,907
Shall we head back?

16
00:00:37,907 --> 00:00:40,867
This bread is famous at Songjeong Station.

17
00:00:40,867 --> 00:00:43,002
[Got some precious bread as a gift too]
- Are you sure I can take this? - Yeah, eat up.

18
00:00:43,002 --> 00:00:44,704
Hope your day's a happy one.

19
00:00:44,704 --> 00:00:46,179
[Off the warm bus, on to the next stop]

20
00:00:47,373 --> 00:00:49,461
[Boseong tea fields full of green romance]
This is unreal.

21
00:00:49,461 --> 00:00:51,077
Those were happy times.

22
00:00:51,077 --> 00:00:54,113
[Romance even sparks love talk]

23
00:00:54,113 --> 00:00:56,041
Hurry, snap the photo, snap it!

24
00:00:56,041 --> 00:00:57,850
[Hopping the bus to their last stop, Yulpo]
Three of us, paying cash.

25
00:00:57,850 --> 00:01:00,620
How many stops till Yulpo?

26
00:01:00,620 --> 00:01:03,890
[Winding through the mountain roads]

27
00:01:03,890 --> 00:01:06,225
[Their stop comes into view soon]

28
00:01:06,225 --> 00:01:08,235
This is where you get off.

29
00:01:08,235 --> 00:01:09,595
- Time to get off?
- Thanks so much.

30
00:01:09,595 --> 00:01:11,264
[Arrived at Yulpo Beach bus stop]

31
00:01:11,264 --> 00:01:14,300
[The Yulpo sculpture welcoming them]

32
00:01:14,300 --> 00:01:16,040
[Right up his alley]
I love Yul for you.

33
00:01:16,040 --> 00:01:18,756
- This place is seriously charming.
- Yeah.

34
00:01:18,756 --> 00:01:20,840
The town's adorable.

35
00:01:20,840 --> 00:01:23,241
So where are you all headed right now?

36
00:01:23,241 --> 00:01:24,277
A guesthouse?

37
00:01:24,277 --> 00:01:25,377
- We're looking for a guesthouse.
- Yeah.

38
00:01:25,377 --> 00:01:27,277
- Trying to find a place to stay first.
- Got it.

39
00:01:27,277 --> 00:01:29,749
But your phone...
you haven't pulled it out yet?

40
00:01:29,749 --> 00:01:30,474
[Right, about that...]

41
00:01:30,474 --> 00:01:32,955
- The phone...
- Oh right, we actually have phones.

42
00:01:32,955 --> 00:01:33,915
We had them?

43
00:01:33,915 --> 00:01:35,833
A place like that Davichi Condo

44
00:01:35,833 --> 00:01:37,927
- probably isn't pricey either.
- Davichi Condo?

45
00:01:37,927 --> 00:01:39,215
Did you check on your phone?

46
00:01:39,215 --> 00:01:40,375
Nope, just spotted it over there.

47
00:01:40,375 --> 00:01:43,396
- She just looked around.
- I just looked around.

48
00:01:43,396 --> 00:01:46,200
[Yulpo Auto Camping, Boseong Davichi Condo]
[Sharp-eyed Po-po]

49
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:47,433
It's off-season.

50
00:01:47,433 --> 00:01:50,336
[Quiet beachside since it's off-season]

51
00:01:50,336 --> 00:01:51,726
- Hey, but...
- Yeah?

52
00:01:51,726 --> 00:01:54,440
- Guesthouses aren't exactly cheap.
- Yeah.

53
00:01:54,440 --> 00:01:56,117
- How much?
- 160,000 won.

54
00:01:56,117 --> 00:01:58,144
[Stunned]
- Huh? That's pricey. - Yeah.

55
00:01:58,144 --> 00:02:00,193
[Tattling immediately]
The guesthouse runs 160,000 won.

56
00:02:00,193 --> 00:02:02,276
[Current balance: 264,210 won]
- Per night? - Yeah.

57
00:02:02,276 --> 00:02:06,586
In that case, Woo Shik,
look up Davichi Condo over there.

58
00:02:06,586 --> 00:02:07,586
It's right there.

59
00:02:07,586 --> 00:02:09,046
[Searching the place they spotted earlier]

60
00:02:09,046 --> 00:02:12,592
Davichi Condo, 100,000, 110,000 won.

61
00:02:12,592 --> 00:02:13,693
[Yikes]

62
00:02:13,693 --> 00:02:16,116
- For one room? Steep.
- Yeah.

63
00:02:16,116 --> 00:02:18,230
- Let me try Boseong Haetsal Guesthouse.
- Sure.

64
00:02:18,230 --> 00:02:21,487
[Panic sets in, full search mode on]

65
00:02:21,487 --> 00:02:22,768
On the expensive side, huh?

66
00:02:22,768 --> 00:02:24,067
[Online rates pricier than expected]

67
00:02:24,067 --> 00:02:27,147
Should we try asking somewhere like that?

68
00:02:27,147 --> 00:02:29,368
[Pivoting hard to in-person hunting]
- Ask first? - See what it costs?

69
00:02:29,368 --> 00:02:30,744
Let's go ask.

70
00:02:32,402 --> 00:02:34,793
[Door locked tight]

71
00:02:34,793 --> 00:02:35,907
It's locked.

72
00:02:35,907 --> 00:02:37,807
- Keep going. Head out.
- Locked.

73
00:02:37,807 --> 00:02:39,986
Down this road?

74
00:02:39,986 --> 00:02:41,159
Shall we?

75
00:02:41,159 --> 00:02:42,588
This way...

76
00:02:42,588 --> 00:02:45,458
[Following the path, spotted a small building]

77
00:02:45,458 --> 00:02:46,993
[Stumbled onto a tourist info center]
- Should we check inside? - Should we ask here?

78
00:02:46,993 --> 00:02:48,537
Here.

79
00:02:48,537 --> 00:02:51,277
- Hello there. Got a quick question.
- Sure.

80
00:02:51,277 --> 00:02:53,071
We're looking for a guesthouse

81
00:02:53,071 --> 00:02:55,158
- or somewhere to stay.
- Yes.

82
00:02:55,158 --> 00:02:57,078
Somewhere cheap, maybe...

83
00:02:57,078 --> 00:02:59,026
- Got any info like that?
- Cheap info?

84
00:02:59,026 --> 00:03:01,393
One moment.

85
00:03:01,393 --> 00:03:03,576
[The staff member comes out personally]
- On this pamphlet here... - Yes.

86
00:03:03,576 --> 00:03:05,899
The pamphlet's got everything
listed right here.

87
00:03:05,899 --> 00:03:07,580
Guesthouses lined up right here on this side.

88
00:03:07,580 --> 00:03:08,827
[Scored a precious guesthouse map!]

89
00:03:08,827 --> 00:03:11,024
- And...
- Thanks so much for the help.

90
00:03:11,024 --> 00:03:13,126
- Just doing my job.
- Right.

91
00:03:13,126 --> 00:03:14,159
[Pro]

92
00:03:14,159 --> 00:03:16,393
[Just doing the job, that's all...]
- Fair enough. - It's my job.

93
00:03:16,393 --> 00:03:17,959
- Thanks again.
- Thank you.

94
00:03:17,959 --> 00:03:20,059
Our Boseong's looking brighter, huh?

95
00:03:20,059 --> 00:03:22,161
[After grateful help from the Boseong pro]

96
00:03:22,161 --> 00:03:23,393
Looks like...

97
00:03:23,393 --> 00:03:26,732
- The guesthouses are all over on that side.
- Oh yeah?

98
00:03:26,732 --> 00:03:28,167
Salt in the air.

99
00:03:28,167 --> 00:03:30,861
- Want to peek at the ocean first?
- Let's go.

100
00:03:30,861 --> 00:03:33,509
- These are all phone-only places, huh?
- Hi there.

101
00:03:33,509 --> 00:03:35,430
- What's your name?
- Leo.

102
00:03:35,430 --> 00:03:36,975
- Hi, Leo.
- Leo.

103
00:03:36,975 --> 00:03:38,110
How old is Leo?

104
00:03:38,110 --> 00:03:39,649
Nine.

105
00:03:39,649 --> 00:03:41,614
Your Korean's pretty good.

106
00:03:41,614 --> 00:03:43,649
[Korean-savvy pup, Leo, nine years old]

107
00:03:43,649 --> 00:03:45,549
This spot's pretty too.

108
00:03:45,549 --> 00:03:47,286
The sea's so calm.

109
00:03:47,286 --> 00:03:51,424
[3:40 PM, Yulpo Beach]

110
00:03:51,424 --> 00:03:53,259
Seriously still water.

111
00:03:53,259 --> 00:03:55,495
For real.

112
00:03:55,495 --> 00:03:57,663
There's a lighthouse over there.

113
00:03:57,663 --> 00:04:00,066
[Soaking in the breezy view,
but only briefly...]

114
00:04:00,066 --> 00:04:02,180
[Looking around...]

115
00:04:02,180 --> 00:04:04,870
- Not quite what we pictured.
- Right.

116
00:04:04,870 --> 00:04:07,640
[Feels kind of empty...]

117
00:04:07,640 --> 00:04:11,346
[Off-season weekday means
hardly anyone at the beach...]

118
00:04:11,346 --> 00:04:12,544
What are they building here?

119
00:04:12,544 --> 00:04:15,460
[Plus, a tourist complex under construction]
They're really developing this place.

120
00:04:15,460 --> 00:04:18,180
Hey, at least we made it to the sea.

121
00:04:18,180 --> 00:04:20,653
- But for sure, this area...
- Yeah.

122
00:04:20,653 --> 00:04:22,971
- The South Sea is definitely...
- Jeollanam-do.

123
00:04:22,971 --> 00:04:24,931
Why aren't there any waves?

124
00:04:24,931 --> 00:04:27,526
All the islands are blocking them.

125
00:04:27,526 --> 00:04:31,460
[The three stroll along the calm sea]
Yeah, looking out, it's all islands.

126
00:04:31,460 --> 00:04:33,465
What's that phone doing there?

127
00:04:35,901 --> 00:04:37,036
[Phone spotted on the sand]

128
00:04:37,036 --> 00:04:39,638
Wait, isn't that theirs?

129
00:04:39,638 --> 00:04:40,970
Excuse me.

130
00:04:40,970 --> 00:04:42,893
Is this maybe...

131
00:04:42,893 --> 00:04:45,593
What? Oh! Hey, your phone!

132
00:04:45,593 --> 00:04:46,645
That's mine?

133
00:04:46,645 --> 00:04:49,080
- Thank you so much.
- No problem.

134
00:04:49,726 --> 00:04:52,126
[Giggling]

135
00:04:52,126 --> 00:04:54,992
Whoa, finding a phone in the sand.

136
00:04:54,992 --> 00:04:57,827
[A girl who almost lost her phone]
If I hadn't been here, her phone would've...

137
00:04:57,827 --> 00:04:59,592
"Where'd it go?"

138
00:04:59,592 --> 00:05:02,725
[Thanks, Uncle Seo Jun!]

139
00:05:02,725 --> 00:05:03,958
Don't they have stuff like that?

140
00:05:03,958 --> 00:05:06,799
Above a sashimi place like that,
isn't that a guesthouse?

141
00:05:06,799 --> 00:05:08,201
Right.

142
00:05:08,201 --> 00:05:09,999
- Above the sashimi place there.
- Yeah.

143
00:05:09,999 --> 00:05:11,560
[Walking the beach, spotted a guesthouse]
Should we try asking somewhere like that?

144
00:05:11,560 --> 00:05:15,026
Above the sashimi place,
the sign says guesthouse.

145
00:05:15,026 --> 00:05:16,142
- Sure does.
- Yeah.

146
00:05:16,142 --> 00:05:18,077
- This way.
- These are all guesthouses.

147
00:05:18,077 --> 00:05:19,512
- Yeah, keep going.
- For sure.

148
00:05:19,512 --> 00:05:20,999
This way? Down here?

149
00:05:20,999 --> 00:05:23,793
Let's ask around.

150
00:05:23,793 --> 00:05:26,352
[Lodging hunt, round 2]
- Alright. - Quick scan to the right.

151
00:05:26,352 --> 00:05:29,099
- Let's try that guesthouse, Woo Shik.
- Right.

152
00:05:29,099 --> 00:05:31,590
Hope they have rooms.

153
00:05:32,579 --> 00:05:34,560
Is this place even open?

154
00:05:34,560 --> 00:05:37,017
- Closed today?
- What?

155
00:05:37,017 --> 00:05:38,898
Oh, the sashimi place.

156
00:05:38,898 --> 00:05:41,333
[Closed today]
The guesthouse is closed, too.

157
00:05:41,333 --> 00:05:44,010
[Cruel closed sign]

158
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:46,105
- Should we call?
- Yeah.

159
00:05:46,105 --> 00:05:47,940
[Trying the contact number]

160
00:05:47,940 --> 00:05:49,593
Hi, hello? So right now,

161
00:05:49,593 --> 00:05:53,177
we're standing outside the guesthouse,
any chance of staying tonight?

162
00:05:53,177 --> 00:05:54,678
<i>Sorry, we're not open today.</i>

163
00:05:54,678 --> 00:05:56,478
- Oh, closed today?
<i>- Yes.</i>

164
00:05:56,478 --> 00:05:58,493
Alright, got it.

165
00:05:58,493 --> 00:05:59,752
They're closed today.

166
00:05:59,752 --> 00:06:01,754
On to the next one.

167
00:06:01,754 --> 00:06:05,357
Wait, is today some kind of holiday?

168
00:06:06,025 --> 00:06:09,428
[Late February weekday means
a sleepy beach town]

169
00:06:09,428 --> 00:06:11,359
Huh? Closed today.

170
00:06:11,359 --> 00:06:12,809
- Closed today.
- This one too?

171
00:06:12,809 --> 00:06:15,293
But let's try calling.

172
00:06:15,293 --> 00:06:16,769
Call them.

173
00:06:16,769 --> 00:06:18,328
Should we ring them up?

174
00:06:18,328 --> 00:06:20,388
[Can't let it go]
- This place looks decent though. - Right?

175
00:06:20,388 --> 00:06:22,049
Hold on, this one's open though.

176
00:06:22,049 --> 00:06:23,809
Yeah. Should we head in?

177
00:06:23,809 --> 00:06:26,078
[Peeking around]

178
00:06:26,078 --> 00:06:29,909
[The closed sign feels extra brutal today...]

179
00:06:30,950 --> 00:06:33,539
[The owner steps out, hearing voices]

180
00:06:35,860 --> 00:06:37,923
- Ma'am, any rooms tonight?
- What?

181
00:06:37,923 --> 00:06:38,859
- Guesthouse.
- Got rooms?

182
00:06:38,859 --> 00:06:40,532
We're hunting for a place to crash.

183
00:06:40,532 --> 00:06:42,593
- Are you looking for a room?
- Yes.

184
00:06:42,593 --> 00:06:45,126
- The room... bed...
- None left?

185
00:06:45,126 --> 00:06:46,326
The rooms...

186
00:06:46,326 --> 00:06:49,168
Only three bedrooms here, no group room.

187
00:06:49,168 --> 00:06:51,337
[Rooms available!]
- That's fine. - Two rooms are all we need.

188
00:06:51,337 --> 00:06:53,306
- All good.
- Just need two rooms.

189
00:06:53,306 --> 00:06:54,893
- They're available.
- Really?

190
00:06:54,893 --> 00:06:58,544
- Let me open one up so you can see.
- Sure.

191
00:06:58,544 --> 00:07:00,011
[Dazed by the sudden win]
Not bad.

192
00:07:00,011 --> 00:07:03,147
- For this price, it's pretty solid, right?
- Way more than solid.

193
00:07:03,147 --> 00:07:05,584
- You take one, the two of us share one.
- And you two together, yeah.

194
00:07:05,584 --> 00:07:06,860
- I've got the keys.
- Okay.

195
00:07:06,860 --> 00:07:09,693
Hey, I know you, I've seen you plenty on TV.

196
00:07:09,693 --> 00:07:13,058
[The kid she's seen all over TV]
Yeah, nice to meet you.

197
00:07:13,058 --> 00:07:16,293
[Heading up to check out the rooms]

198
00:07:16,293 --> 00:07:19,465
Knew you looked familiar, seen you on TV.

199
00:07:19,465 --> 00:07:22,201
[Sweet owner opens up the first room]

200
00:07:22,201 --> 00:07:24,202
This is awesome.

201
00:07:25,571 --> 00:07:28,040
[Cozy double bedroom vibe]

202
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:29,108
[Table, sofa, TV, mini fridge]

203
00:07:29,108 --> 00:07:30,910
[Fully stocked with furniture and appliances]

204
00:07:30,910 --> 00:07:33,312
[And on top of that...]

205
00:07:33,312 --> 00:07:35,986
[Ocean view comes free]

206
00:07:35,986 --> 00:07:37,516
- This is great.
- Not bad at all.

207
00:07:37,516 --> 00:07:38,393
Nice.

208
00:07:38,393 --> 00:07:40,727
The best views around belong to us.

209
00:07:40,727 --> 00:07:43,356
The view's amazing.

210
00:07:43,356 --> 00:07:46,625
This one works for the two of us.

211
00:07:46,625 --> 00:07:48,394
[Tidy second room for Seo Jun and Woo Shik]

212
00:07:48,394 --> 00:07:50,426
[Ocean view here too]

213
00:07:50,426 --> 00:07:53,999
- If you need one more room...
- Show us one more, please.

214
00:07:53,999 --> 00:07:56,035
[For the crew, checking out the last room]
This one's a city view.

215
00:07:56,035 --> 00:07:58,070
This one's PD Geon Jun's room.

216
00:07:58,070 --> 00:07:59,087
[Slides in]

217
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:02,153
[Three rooms locked in]
Total win.

218
00:08:02,153 --> 00:08:03,493
- So then...
- Yes.

219
00:08:03,493 --> 00:08:05,893
The big question now is the price...

220
00:08:05,893 --> 00:08:07,026
- Price?
- Yes.

221
00:08:07,026 --> 00:08:09,181
- 40,000 each.
- Okay.

222
00:08:09,181 --> 00:08:12,685
40, 40 makes 80, plus 30 brings 110.

223
00:08:12,685 --> 00:08:13,726
[Oh my]

224
00:08:13,726 --> 00:08:17,256
This one's city view, so 30,000.

225
00:08:17,256 --> 00:08:20,125
[Expense log, guesthouse: -80,000 won,
Balance: 184,210 won]

226
00:08:20,125 --> 00:08:22,393
For the price, this is incredible, right?

227
00:08:22,393 --> 00:08:23,996
So cozy.

228
00:08:23,996 --> 00:08:26,105
And it's an ocean view.

229
00:08:26,105 --> 00:08:27,766
It's an ocean view.

230
00:08:27,766 --> 00:08:30,935
Ocean view? For 40,000?

231
00:08:31,737 --> 00:08:32,927
Insane deal.

232
00:08:32,927 --> 00:08:37,159
So as today's gone on,
we've got too much cash left over.

233
00:08:37,159 --> 00:08:41,726
All that's left is spending it.

234
00:08:41,726 --> 00:08:46,051
The plan is just to
blow through our cash today.

235
00:08:46,051 --> 00:08:48,520
[Seo Jun and Woo Shik resting in their room]

236
00:08:48,520 --> 00:08:50,337
[Click]

237
00:08:50,337 --> 00:08:52,191
Oh, hey.

238
00:08:52,191 --> 00:08:54,426
You picked up someone's phone or what?

239
00:08:54,426 --> 00:08:55,438
Some little kid, yeah.

240
00:08:55,438 --> 00:08:58,426
So those two little girls came up like this,

241
00:08:58,426 --> 00:09:00,397
- all shy and fidgety.
- Yeah.

242
00:09:00,397 --> 00:09:03,135
Then they said thanks a million
and handed me this,

243
00:09:03,135 --> 00:09:05,037
asked me to pass it along.

244
00:09:05,037 --> 00:09:07,397
- Super grateful.
- Mychew?

245
00:09:07,397 --> 00:09:09,575
They were just too cute.

246
00:09:09,575 --> 00:09:11,578
Adorable.

247
00:09:11,578 --> 00:09:13,762
[The sweet little thank-you crew]
- Thank you. - Yeah.

248
00:09:13,762 --> 00:09:15,726
Let's pop a Mychew.

249
00:09:15,726 --> 00:09:16,782
Mychew.

250
00:09:16,782 --> 00:09:20,240
[Sweet Mychew shared all around]

251
00:09:20,240 --> 00:09:24,623
Hey, mystery middle-school-aged cuties,

252
00:09:24,623 --> 00:09:26,593
the thing is,

253
00:09:26,593 --> 00:09:30,529
we crash on sugar a lot
during all this traveling,

254
00:09:30,529 --> 00:09:33,026
so I'll ration these till the trip ends

255
00:09:33,026 --> 00:09:34,841
and enjoy every one.

256
00:09:34,841 --> 00:09:36,402
Really appreciate it.

257
00:09:36,402 --> 00:09:37,742
[Bashful]

258
00:09:37,742 --> 00:09:39,860
Time to hunt down some food.

259
00:09:39,860 --> 00:09:41,665
[Up next: planning dinner]
- Tonight. - Yeah.

260
00:09:41,665 --> 00:09:42,665
Let's do sashimi.

261
00:09:42,665 --> 00:09:44,176
- Sashimi it is.
- I'm in.

262
00:09:44,176 --> 00:09:46,120
- Let's flex a little tonight.
- Yeah.

263
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:47,180
For real.

264
00:09:47,180 --> 00:09:49,721
- Shall I look up restaurants?
- Yeah.

265
00:09:49,721 --> 00:09:51,921
[Searching with phone perks]
Hold on, Boseong...

266
00:09:51,921 --> 00:09:55,560
That place has way more reviews
than anywhere else.

267
00:09:55,560 --> 00:09:57,426
- Gaet*eul?
- Yeah.

268
00:09:57,426 --> 00:09:59,126
[Option 1. The recommended 'G' restaurant]
By a mile.

269
00:09:59,126 --> 00:10:02,102
That grandma from earlier
mentioned this one too.

270
00:10:02,102 --> 00:10:04,182
- Which one?
- Suileok* raw fish restaurant.

271
00:10:04,182 --> 00:10:07,222
[Option 2. Another recommended 'S' restaurant]
Suileok* raw fish restaurant.

272
00:10:07,222 --> 00:10:08,967
Let me check out Man* Hall here.

273
00:10:08,967 --> 00:10:11,301
[Option 3. The 'M' restaurant Seo Jun found]
The name's nice.

274
00:10:11,301 --> 00:10:13,222
[An endless list of restaurants]
I spotted Seong** on the way in.

275
00:10:13,222 --> 00:10:15,207
- Haeng*?
- Haeng* raw fish restaurant.

276
00:10:15,207 --> 00:10:17,092
But we should check if they're open.

277
00:10:17,092 --> 00:10:19,707
[Paranoid about closures]
- Give them a call. - I'll try them.

278
00:10:19,707 --> 00:10:22,693
[Dialing right away]
The ringtone sounds old-school.

279
00:10:22,693 --> 00:10:24,716
<i>- Hello.</i>
- Hi, ma'am.

280
00:10:24,716 --> 00:10:27,047
Are you open today?

281
00:10:27,047 --> 00:10:29,421
[Owner 1]
<i>Oh, we're closed.</i>

282
00:10:29,421 --> 00:10:31,757
Okay, got it.

283
00:10:31,757 --> 00:10:33,359
[Still stuck in the closure swamp...]
Sure.

284
00:10:33,359 --> 00:10:35,047
Is everyone closed today or something?

285
00:10:35,047 --> 00:10:37,187
Why is no one open today?

286
00:10:37,187 --> 00:10:39,832
[Late-Feb weekday, off-season, many shops closed]
Off-season weekdays, looks like a lot of them

287
00:10:39,832 --> 00:10:41,667
take the day off.

288
00:10:41,667 --> 00:10:44,227
[But even after that...]
Now try calling Man* Hall too.

289
00:10:44,227 --> 00:10:46,792
[Owner 2]
<i>- Ah, raw fish, we don't serve that.</i> - Right.

290
00:10:46,792 --> 00:10:48,726
[Owner 3]
<i>We're not doing raw fish right now.</i>

291
00:10:48,726 --> 00:10:49,842
<i>We don't carry it.</i>

292
00:10:49,842 --> 00:10:52,344
[Strike out, no raw fish]
I see. Thanks anyway.

293
00:10:52,344 --> 00:10:54,259
Due to the owner's request or non-registration,

294
00:10:54,259 --> 00:10:56,115
the phone number isn't available.

295
00:10:56,115 --> 00:10:58,468
[Strike out, no number]

296
00:11:01,153 --> 00:11:03,092
There's also Boseong Raw Fish Center, right?

297
00:11:03,092 --> 00:11:04,493
Bet that's tasty.

298
00:11:04,493 --> 00:11:06,138
Isn't it where you buy the fish
and they serve it?

299
00:11:06,138 --> 00:11:07,326
Yeah.

300
00:11:07,326 --> 00:11:09,560
But the raw fish center is probably open, so...

301
00:11:09,560 --> 00:11:10,860
- Let's go.
- No need to even call.

302
00:11:10,860 --> 00:11:12,313
- Right now.
- Off to the raw fish center.

303
00:11:12,313 --> 00:11:14,366
[Raw fish center it is!]
- Let's head over. - Yeah.

304
00:11:15,159 --> 00:11:18,003
[6:15 PM, Boseong Raw Fish Center]

305
00:11:18,003 --> 00:11:20,430
[Hurrying along]

306
00:11:20,430 --> 00:11:23,159
[A 5-min walk from the lodging]
Boseong, oh, this is it. This is the place.

307
00:11:23,159 --> 00:11:24,526
It's close, huh.

308
00:11:24,526 --> 00:11:26,493
On the first floor...

309
00:11:26,493 --> 00:11:28,060
Do we buy on the first floor?

310
00:11:28,060 --> 00:11:31,549
- Buy downstairs, then up...
- Then head upstairs, right?

311
00:11:32,951 --> 00:11:36,155
[A lively seafood market downstairs]

312
00:11:36,155 --> 00:11:39,324
That's gotta be super fresh.

313
00:11:41,194 --> 00:11:42,959
- Hi there.
- Hello.

314
00:11:42,959 --> 00:11:44,463
[Beelining to the vendor they spotted]
Hi.

315
00:11:44,463 --> 00:11:46,465
- Hello.
- Whoa.

316
00:11:46,465 --> 00:11:48,092
- Whoa.
- Whoa.

317
00:11:48,092 --> 00:11:50,276
- The one with stripes...
- Yes.

318
00:11:50,276 --> 00:11:51,736
Is that a giant grouper?

319
00:11:51,736 --> 00:11:52,757
Isn't it a rockfish?

320
00:11:52,757 --> 00:11:54,236
No, this one, this guy.

321
00:11:54,236 --> 00:11:55,793
That's a striped beakfish.

322
00:11:55,793 --> 00:11:57,136
- Bream.
- Right.

323
00:11:57,136 --> 00:11:59,896
- Isn't this a rockfish?
- That's a black sea bream.

324
00:11:59,896 --> 00:12:01,776
What should we get?

325
00:12:01,776 --> 00:12:03,757
- Striped beakfish is delicious.
- Should we go with striped beakfish?

326
00:12:03,757 --> 00:12:05,896
By the way, how much does this run?

327
00:12:05,896 --> 00:12:08,017
Striped beakfish is 100,000 won per kilo.

328
00:12:08,017 --> 00:12:09,059
- 100,000 won?
- Yes.

329
00:12:09,059 --> 00:12:11,023
- 100,000 won.
- Striped beakfish is tasty too.

330
00:12:11,023 --> 00:12:12,689
[Out of nowhere]

331
00:12:12,689 --> 00:12:14,877
- Can we get one of these too?
- Pen shell?

332
00:12:14,877 --> 00:12:15,560
- What's this?
- A clam?

333
00:12:15,560 --> 00:12:17,536
- That one's a cockle.
- Okay.

334
00:12:17,536 --> 00:12:19,790
[Yumi's seafood pick, cockle meat]
Cockle.

335
00:12:19,790 --> 00:12:20,992
[FLEX dinner order, 1kg beakfish]
Striped beakfish.

336
00:12:20,992 --> 00:12:22,668
- 1kg of striped beakfish.
- Yeah.

337
00:12:22,668 --> 00:12:24,611
- I want this.
- And also.

338
00:12:24,611 --> 00:12:26,471
[FLEX order, beakfish 1kg, cockle 1pk]
- One cockle, right? - Yeah.

339
00:12:26,471 --> 00:12:27,526
[Looking around]

340
00:12:27,526 --> 00:12:28,991
How much for the pen shell?

341
00:12:28,991 --> 00:12:31,471
- 6,000 won each.
- One of these, one pen shell.

342
00:12:31,471 --> 00:12:33,026
[One pen shell]
- Just one? - Yes.

343
00:12:33,026 --> 00:12:35,741
[That's all]
- That'll do for now? - Yeah, that's it.

344
00:12:36,593 --> 00:12:39,116
[Beakfish out first]
Whoa, the big one.

345
00:12:39,116 --> 00:12:40,843
[Speedy bream]

346
00:12:40,843 --> 00:12:42,581
- Where'd it go? Striped beakfish...
- A different one got caught.

347
00:12:42,581 --> 00:12:44,689
is really tough to catch.

348
00:12:45,992 --> 00:12:48,984
[The beakfish that came up looks under 1kg]
- Oh, it's small? - Small.

349
00:12:48,984 --> 00:12:51,359
- She's really good at this.
- Can I give it a try?

350
00:12:51,359 --> 00:12:52,497
Sure, go ahead.

351
00:12:52,497 --> 00:12:54,734
[Taking a bold shot]

352
00:12:54,734 --> 00:12:55,959
Where is it?

353
00:12:55,959 --> 00:12:58,470
It's behind there.

354
00:12:58,470 --> 00:13:00,339
[Nervous...]

355
00:13:00,339 --> 00:13:01,426
[Older two loving Woo Shik's antics]

356
00:13:01,426 --> 00:13:04,044
Think we'll actually get to eat?

357
00:13:04,044 --> 00:13:05,077
There it is.

358
00:13:05,077 --> 00:13:06,259
[Dead serious]

359
00:13:06,259 --> 00:13:08,761
- Right here.
- Here.

360
00:13:09,715 --> 00:13:10,793
[Yes! I caught a striped beakfish!]

361
00:13:10,793 --> 00:13:12,317
He got it.

362
00:13:12,317 --> 00:13:14,152
[Hauled in a big one on the first try]

363
00:13:14,152 --> 00:13:15,721
[Ah... so frustrating...]

364
00:13:15,721 --> 00:13:17,827
- Let's stick with just this.
- Just this one.

365
00:13:17,827 --> 00:13:19,193
- Okay.
- Sure.

366
00:13:19,193 --> 00:13:21,519
- We're paying in cash.
- Cash?

367
00:13:21,519 --> 00:13:24,396
[Dinner: -147,000 won. Balance: 37,210 won]
- Here you go. - Thanks so much.

368
00:13:24,396 --> 00:13:26,999
[Done ordering, heading up to the restaurant]

369
00:13:26,999 --> 00:13:28,500
Oh wait, we still have to pay the table fee.

370
00:13:28,500 --> 00:13:30,726
- Didn't even think about that.
- I totally forgot.

371
00:13:30,726 --> 00:13:31,959
- 6,000 won.
- I think we've got enough.

372
00:13:31,959 --> 00:13:33,860
We're good.

373
00:13:33,860 --> 00:13:34,893
This...

374
00:13:34,893 --> 00:13:36,320
[More orders downstairs means big trouble]
Let's see the side dishes first

375
00:13:36,320 --> 00:13:37,342
then order extras.

376
00:13:37,342 --> 00:13:38,559
Let's go.

377
00:13:38,559 --> 00:13:40,979
- Hello.
- Oh my, hello.

378
00:13:40,979 --> 00:13:43,982
Hold on, so right now we have...

379
00:13:43,982 --> 00:13:45,026
[Rechecking the balance over the table fee]

380
00:13:45,026 --> 00:13:47,860
37,000 won.

381
00:13:47,860 --> 00:13:49,497
- Oh really?
- Yeah.

382
00:13:49,497 --> 00:13:50,298
For now, at least...

383
00:13:50,298 --> 00:13:52,139
- Still enough though.
- Right.

384
00:13:52,139 --> 00:13:53,077
Striped beakfish?

385
00:13:53,077 --> 00:13:54,717
- The striped beakfish is going to be amazing.
- Right.

386
00:13:54,717 --> 00:13:56,293
- Striped beakfish is delicious.
- Striped beakfish?

387
00:13:56,293 --> 00:13:58,330
- You ordered striped beakfish?
- Yes.

388
00:13:58,330 --> 00:14:00,533
- That's super pricey even in Seoul.
- The size...

389
00:14:00,533 --> 00:14:02,226
Huge flex today.

390
00:14:02,226 --> 00:14:04,536
- Totally.
- For real.

391
00:14:04,536 --> 00:14:06,059
[Trembling]
This is going to taste so good.

392
00:14:06,059 --> 00:14:08,239
Should we try the sea pineapple?

393
00:14:08,940 --> 00:14:11,576
[Sea pineapple to cleanse the palate]

394
00:14:11,576 --> 00:14:13,383
Okay.

395
00:14:14,146 --> 00:14:15,580
Cheers.

396
00:14:15,580 --> 00:14:18,585
[Pairing the sides with a glass of soju]

397
00:14:19,383 --> 00:14:21,687
It's sweet.

398
00:14:21,687 --> 00:14:23,222
Here it comes.

399
00:14:23,222 --> 00:14:26,591
[The peak of the flex arrives]
- Whoa. - The pricey one.

400
00:14:26,591 --> 00:14:28,223
Top-tier.

401
00:14:28,223 --> 00:14:29,394
It's here.

402
00:14:29,394 --> 00:14:30,912
[The class of a premium fish, shining]

403
00:14:30,912 --> 00:14:34,560
[Beakfish stands out from the color alone]

404
00:14:35,326 --> 00:14:37,335
[Bland and dry]
Anybody got salt?

405
00:14:37,937 --> 00:14:39,705
[Bye to the egg-eating days]
It's spilling everywhere.

406
00:14:40,372 --> 00:14:42,074
[Plus the triangle gimbap and sandwiches]

407
00:14:42,074 --> 00:14:44,010
[Now it's farewell]

408
00:14:44,876 --> 00:14:46,845
[Dipping it lightly in soy sauce]

409
00:14:46,845 --> 00:14:49,614
[Savoring the taste of the flex]

410
00:14:49,614 --> 00:14:51,690
It's so chewy.

411
00:14:54,159 --> 00:14:56,221
[The taste of luxury]
Seriously chewy.

412
00:14:56,221 --> 00:14:57,889
[Nodding]

413
00:14:57,889 --> 00:14:59,725
It's delicious.

414
00:15:00,859 --> 00:15:03,126
[This is it]

415
00:15:03,126 --> 00:15:04,836
It's incredible.

416
00:15:05,897 --> 00:15:07,927
[Perfect mirrors of each other]

417
00:15:07,927 --> 00:15:09,326
Our menu is different every single day.

418
00:15:09,326 --> 00:15:10,936
- Is it good?
- Yeah.

419
00:15:10,936 --> 00:15:12,920
We really flexed hard today.

420
00:15:12,920 --> 00:15:14,880
Nice.

421
00:15:14,880 --> 00:15:16,740
If you get the car benefit tomorrow,
where are you heading?

422
00:15:16,740 --> 00:15:17,976
- Yeongdeok.
- Yeongdeok.

423
00:15:17,976 --> 00:15:19,893
[Yeongdeok keeps coming up]

424
00:15:19,893 --> 00:15:21,860
Yeongdeok, for reasons unknown.

425
00:15:21,860 --> 00:15:24,349
- For snow crab bread.
- And then Samcheok.

426
00:15:24,349 --> 00:15:26,829
[Older sister's got it all planned out]
That sounds great.

427
00:15:26,829 --> 00:15:28,660
If we score the car,

428
00:15:28,660 --> 00:15:30,793
- Straight...
- we move on,

429
00:15:30,793 --> 00:15:32,263
or else

430
00:15:32,263 --> 00:15:35,527
let's hunt for an activity nearby
and ditch this town.

431
00:15:35,527 --> 00:15:38,726
[Stomachs full, off to chase some dopamine]

432
00:15:38,726 --> 00:15:41,226
So like, around here, maybe

433
00:15:41,226 --> 00:15:43,402
something like bungee jumping.

434
00:15:43,402 --> 00:15:44,318
Or...

435
00:15:44,318 --> 00:15:47,173
- Can you do that?
- For instance,

436
00:15:47,173 --> 00:15:50,026
- ATVs or stuff like that.
- ATVs.

437
00:15:50,026 --> 00:15:51,810
Let's chase down some activities.

438
00:15:51,810 --> 00:15:53,844
I'm all for it, activities sound great.

439
00:15:53,844 --> 00:15:55,664
Let's look up some activities.

440
00:15:55,664 --> 00:15:57,992
There's an amusement park in Gyeongju.

441
00:15:57,992 --> 00:16:01,904
[Far west and far east]
Gyeongju is all the way over this way.

442
00:16:01,904 --> 00:16:03,688
There's one in Daejeon too.

443
00:16:03,688 --> 00:16:06,593
For starters,
we need to swing by Boseong Station,

444
00:16:06,593 --> 00:16:08,760
then head back into town.

445
00:16:08,760 --> 00:16:10,193
[Sliding in]

446
00:16:10,193 --> 00:16:12,597
[The pot arrives]
Didn't you scream yesterday morning too?

447
00:16:12,597 --> 00:16:15,066
[As for this pot...]

448
00:16:15,066 --> 00:16:20,071
[Pure south-coast style, cockle shabu-style]

449
00:16:20,071 --> 00:16:21,540
[Standing up]

450
00:16:21,540 --> 00:16:23,007
Whoa.

451
00:16:23,667 --> 00:16:26,143
What's all in here?

452
00:16:26,847 --> 00:16:28,747
Looks like they made it
clear-broth style, right?

453
00:16:28,747 --> 00:16:30,767
[Broth from veggies, shellfish, fish bones]

454
00:16:30,767 --> 00:16:32,184
- This is really...
- It's going to taste so good.

455
00:16:32,184 --> 00:16:33,518
[Cockle goes in]

456
00:16:33,518 --> 00:16:35,308
I don't think I've ever had this before.

457
00:16:35,308 --> 00:16:38,223
It's really good, kind of sweet.

458
00:16:38,223 --> 00:16:39,496
[Scoop out the lightly cooked cockle]

459
00:16:39,496 --> 00:16:40,992
Thanks.

460
00:16:40,992 --> 00:16:43,008
[As always, age first, Yumi]

461
00:16:43,795 --> 00:16:45,437
[Slurp]

462
00:16:46,255 --> 00:16:47,266
It looks done, right?

463
00:16:47,266 --> 00:16:48,533
Yeah, it's tasty.

464
00:16:48,533 --> 00:16:50,455
[Cockle first-timer Woo Shik tries a bite]

465
00:16:51,103 --> 00:16:52,204
Sweet, isn't it?

466
00:16:52,204 --> 00:16:54,773
- It's really tender.
- Yeah?

467
00:16:54,773 --> 00:16:56,842
[Sweet and silky]

468
00:16:56,842 --> 00:16:58,827
- You're right.
- Sweet, right?

469
00:16:58,827 --> 00:17:00,678
It's so good.

470
00:17:01,354 --> 00:17:03,876
[Now the cooked pen shell adductor]
Okay, let's give this one a try.

471
00:17:03,876 --> 00:17:06,896
[Already impressed]
There's no way this isn't delicious.

472
00:17:06,896 --> 00:17:09,554
- The pen shell was 6,000 won each, right?
- Yeah.

473
00:17:09,554 --> 00:17:11,488
[Inhaling the pen shell]

474
00:17:14,259 --> 00:17:16,358
[Headbanging]

475
00:17:18,059 --> 00:17:19,112
The cash that's left over,

476
00:17:19,112 --> 00:17:21,299
let's just spend the rest of it on that.

477
00:17:21,299 --> 00:17:22,744
[Ready to go all-in on pen shell]

478
00:17:22,744 --> 00:17:23,593
- Huh?
- 12,000 won.

479
00:17:23,593 --> 00:17:24,970
Sure.

480
00:17:24,970 --> 00:17:26,760
It's the pen shell.

481
00:17:26,760 --> 00:17:28,039
I'm a pen shell person.

482
00:17:28,039 --> 00:17:29,910
[Choi Woo Shik, Pen shell]

483
00:17:29,910 --> 00:17:31,956
I love this one too.

484
00:17:32,577 --> 00:17:36,047
[Jung Yumi, Cockle]

485
00:17:36,047 --> 00:17:37,483
[One pen shell left]

486
00:17:37,483 --> 00:17:38,750
Then you take this last one.

487
00:17:38,750 --> 00:17:40,204
- It's okay.
- Woo Shik loves it, give it to him.

488
00:17:40,204 --> 00:17:43,923
No, you've got to blanch it first.

489
00:17:43,923 --> 00:17:45,357
But apparently you can eat it raw too.

490
00:17:45,357 --> 00:17:46,825
[Dinner wraps with the last pen shell...]

491
00:17:47,726 --> 00:17:50,383
[Night settles over the Boseong sea]

492
00:17:52,155 --> 00:17:55,834
[The trio heads back to the lodging...]

493
00:17:55,834 --> 00:17:57,936
[Click]

494
00:17:57,936 --> 00:18:00,986
[The younger ones step into the room]

495
00:18:00,986 --> 00:18:02,326
Let's take a shower first.

496
00:18:02,326 --> 00:18:04,135
- Okay.
- Sure.

497
00:18:04,776 --> 00:18:07,675
[Weren't you supposed to be showering?]

498
00:18:08,413 --> 00:18:11,864
[Meanwhile, Po-po faces the camera]

499
00:18:14,899 --> 00:18:18,293
[What Yumi had been itching to try]
- Hey, I'll try the 35% smile. - Okay.

500
00:18:18,293 --> 00:18:19,992
That's not it.

501
00:18:19,992 --> 00:18:21,092
Ouch, my back.

502
00:18:21,092 --> 00:18:22,855
[Failing at the smile game, Yumi]

503
00:18:22,855 --> 00:18:25,760
[Drops by the boys' room to say night]
- Did you shower? - Just now.

504
00:18:25,760 --> 00:18:27,098
- Sleep well.
- Yeah.

505
00:18:27,098 --> 00:18:28,934
Goodnight.

506
00:18:28,934 --> 00:18:30,969
[And so the Boseong night passes]

507
00:18:30,969 --> 00:18:34,940
[Morning of trip day four]

508
00:18:34,940 --> 00:18:36,975
[9:50 AM, Yumi's room]

509
00:18:36,975 --> 00:18:38,343
[Tossing]

510
00:18:38,343 --> 00:18:40,912
[Sigh]

511
00:18:40,912 --> 00:18:42,280
[Just when it seemed she'd sighed...]

512
00:18:42,280 --> 00:18:44,950
[Springs up]

513
00:18:44,950 --> 00:18:46,818
[Po-po feels stiff all over]

514
00:18:46,818 --> 00:18:48,119
[Stiff]

515
00:18:48,119 --> 00:18:49,535
Oh man.

516
00:18:50,221 --> 00:18:51,860
[Emergency joint check via stretching]

517
00:18:51,860 --> 00:18:53,558
This is rough.

518
00:18:53,558 --> 00:18:55,961
[A quiet truth slipping out...]

519
00:18:55,961 --> 00:18:59,431
[Kicking off by folding the bedding...]

520
00:18:59,431 --> 00:19:03,034
[Picking up the pace, launching day four]

521
00:19:03,034 --> 00:19:05,637
[Neatly folded, one down]

522
00:19:05,637 --> 00:19:09,174
[Next blanket, come on in]

523
00:19:09,174 --> 00:19:12,711
[Sent back to its original bed]

524
00:19:12,711 --> 00:19:16,414
[Curtains wide open, photosynthesis on]

525
00:19:16,414 --> 00:19:19,718
[Seo Jun's done showering, Woo Shik's groggy]

526
00:19:19,718 --> 00:19:23,188
I really hope the phone doesn't come up today.

527
00:19:23,188 --> 00:19:26,002
[Woo Shik mumbles his wish, off to shower...]

528
00:19:26,691 --> 00:19:29,594
[Po-po still deep in cleanup mode...]

529
00:19:29,594 --> 00:19:32,530
[The merchant packs everything up first]

530
00:19:32,530 --> 00:19:36,635
[Done tidying, Po-po heads off to shower]

531
00:19:36,635 --> 00:19:39,938
[What's this guy up to...?]

532
00:19:39,938 --> 00:19:43,074
[Selfie mode]
[How he works the phone benefit]

533
00:19:43,074 --> 00:19:47,112
[Rock-steady comfort, blow-dry complete]

534
00:19:47,112 --> 00:19:50,949
[Woo Shik settles in to dry his hair too...]

535
00:19:50,949 --> 00:19:52,317
[Mirror mode via the TV screen]

536
00:19:52,317 --> 00:19:54,335
[Definitely bigger though...]

537
00:19:55,027 --> 00:19:56,988
Please let us get the car.

538
00:19:57,989 --> 00:20:00,326
I really want the car today.

539
00:20:00,326 --> 00:20:02,992
If we score the car, hitting up some activities
would be way easier.

540
00:20:02,992 --> 00:20:04,297
Exactly.

541
00:20:05,563 --> 00:20:07,899
[Po-po is somehow already ready]

542
00:20:07,899 --> 00:20:10,535
[She grabs her stuff and heads off somewhere]

543
00:20:10,535 --> 00:20:11,870
[Straight to the next room]

544
00:20:11,870 --> 00:20:14,293
- All done?
- Yeah.

545
00:20:14,293 --> 00:20:15,775
Oh please.

546
00:20:15,775 --> 00:20:18,009
If it's the phone again today,
that'd be the worst.

547
00:20:18,009 --> 00:20:19,444
Please.

548
00:20:19,444 --> 00:20:22,514
[They step out making their nth wish]

549
00:20:22,514 --> 00:20:24,716
Please, just for today.

550
00:20:24,716 --> 00:20:26,960
[Trio comes out chanting the same wish]

551
00:20:26,960 --> 00:20:28,193
Please give us the car.

552
00:20:28,193 --> 00:20:30,488
Just for today.

553
00:20:30,488 --> 00:20:31,756
So, did everyone sleep well?

554
00:20:31,756 --> 00:20:34,011
- Yes.
- How was the room here?

555
00:20:34,610 --> 00:20:38,293
- I slept a ton.
- It was wonderful.

556
00:20:38,293 --> 00:20:40,143
Day four, before I hand over the allowance,

557
00:20:40,143 --> 00:20:42,174
how much do you have left?

558
00:20:42,174 --> 00:20:44,760
We flexed pretty hard yesterday.

559
00:20:44,760 --> 00:20:47,473
- Even so, there's 12,000 won left.
- Oh, nice.

560
00:20:47,473 --> 00:20:49,706
[Not bad for going in on striped beakfish]

561
00:20:49,706 --> 00:20:53,011
I'll go ahead and give you 300,000 won now.

562
00:20:53,011 --> 00:20:54,946
[Day 4 allowance of 300,000 won handed over]

563
00:20:54,946 --> 00:20:56,548
[Expense log, Day 4 allowance: +300,000 won,
Balance: 312,210 won]

564
00:20:56,548 --> 00:20:58,560
- Got it.
- It's also time for another benefit draw.

565
00:20:58,560 --> 00:21:01,258
The 24 hours on yesterday's phone are up,
so let's do it again.

566
00:21:01,258 --> 00:21:02,938
- Please, just take it.
- If you give it back...

567
00:21:02,938 --> 00:21:05,358
- Please, just take it already.
- Let's never turn it on again.

568
00:21:05,358 --> 00:21:07,777
- I never want to see it again.
- Truly.

569
00:21:07,777 --> 00:21:09,994
[Scary]
Catch you in Seoul, for real.

570
00:21:09,994 --> 00:21:12,197
[Declaring a breakup and powering off]
Please stay away.

571
00:21:12,197 --> 00:21:14,637
Don't come back, please.

572
00:21:14,637 --> 00:21:16,092
[All three turn in their phones without regret]
Thanks.

573
00:21:16,092 --> 00:21:17,293
The phones are collected,

574
00:21:17,293 --> 00:21:20,279
and now we're onto the third benefit draw,

575
00:21:20,279 --> 00:21:24,059
but you've drawn the phone
two times in a row so far.

576
00:21:24,059 --> 00:21:25,076
Right.

577
00:21:25,076 --> 00:21:27,359
[A bond no one asked for that won't quit...]
Same three again today,

578
00:21:27,359 --> 00:21:30,081
We're doing it with car, lodging, and phone,

579
00:21:30,081 --> 00:21:33,762
so today, each of you tells me
what you absolutely want to draw.

580
00:21:33,762 --> 00:21:35,226
- Don't even say it.
- Aren't we all on the same page?

581
00:21:35,226 --> 00:21:37,088
- Today...
- She said don't say it.

582
00:21:37,088 --> 00:21:38,725
Don't say it.

583
00:21:38,725 --> 00:21:40,391
[Trauma]
Don't say it.

584
00:21:40,391 --> 00:21:42,523
- We said it yesterday and...
- I want to draw the phone today.

585
00:21:42,523 --> 00:21:44,897
- I want to draw the phone today.
- I want to draw the phone today.

586
00:21:44,897 --> 00:21:45,897
The phone today.

587
00:21:45,897 --> 00:21:46,847
- Right.
- Phone.

588
00:21:46,847 --> 00:21:48,962
[Three benefit slips are ready...]
Phone, lodging, car.

589
00:21:48,962 --> 00:21:50,401
- These three.
- Okay.

590
00:21:50,401 --> 00:21:53,226
- I'll fold them in front of you again.
- Sure.

591
00:21:53,226 --> 00:21:55,322
Is there anything in the paper bag?

592
00:21:55,322 --> 00:21:56,783
Nothing's in here.

593
00:21:56,783 --> 00:21:58,992
- You're putting them in there?
- Yes.

594
00:21:58,992 --> 00:22:01,112
[Bag turned out, all clean]
- Empty, see. - Okay.

595
00:22:01,112 --> 00:22:02,882
You two aren't secretly magicians, are you?

596
00:22:02,882 --> 00:22:05,732
- Come on.
- You can swap them out if you want.

597
00:22:05,732 --> 00:22:07,752
How about rolling up your sleeves?

598
00:22:07,752 --> 00:22:08,787
[Got it]

599
00:22:08,787 --> 00:22:10,326
[The suspicion born
from two phones in a row...]

600
00:22:10,326 --> 00:22:12,824
Alright. I'll drop these other two in as well.

601
00:22:12,824 --> 00:22:14,875
[The system running transparently
right before their eyes]

602
00:22:14,875 --> 00:22:17,053
So who's drawing today?

603
00:22:17,053 --> 00:22:20,832
- For today...
- Seo Jun's doing it today.

604
00:22:20,832 --> 00:22:23,672
[Today's benefit-draw star]
Should've just gone first on day one.

605
00:22:23,672 --> 00:22:25,927
- I'm picking?
- Yes.

606
00:22:25,927 --> 00:22:28,760
The staff's fate is riding on this.

607
00:22:28,760 --> 00:22:32,352
[Trio's fate is the crew's fate too]
- Oh, please. - Oh, please.

608
00:22:32,352 --> 00:22:34,379
If you draw the phone, we're...

609
00:22:34,379 --> 00:22:36,548
really in for a rough time.

610
00:22:36,548 --> 00:22:39,117
[Thanks to two phone draws in a row]

611
00:22:39,117 --> 00:22:42,255
[Crew vehicles ready, never used]
[Pie in the sky]

612
00:22:42,255 --> 00:22:44,088
Looks like we have to make our way to Boseong.

613
00:22:44,088 --> 00:22:47,781
[Crew tagging along by bus, train, and foot]

614
00:22:47,781 --> 00:22:49,727
Please.

615
00:22:49,727 --> 00:22:51,026
[Seo Jun's hand holds everyone's transport]
Please.

616
00:22:51,026 --> 00:22:52,619
[Just dip in]
Please.

617
00:22:52,619 --> 00:22:54,766
Please, you've got good luck.

618
00:22:54,766 --> 00:22:56,059
- Please, seriously.
- Please.

619
00:22:56,059 --> 00:22:58,059
Check out the faces on those folks.

620
00:22:58,059 --> 00:23:00,240
[Can we please ride the vans today?]
- Please. - Please.

621
00:23:00,240 --> 00:23:03,159
[Everyone's in the same boat...]
- Please. - Ah, please.

622
00:23:03,159 --> 00:23:05,959
[Being extra careful here...]
- Please. - Ah, please.

623
00:23:05,959 --> 00:23:07,827
[The bag's about to give out]

624
00:23:07,827 --> 00:23:08,881
[He picked!]
Seo Jun!

625
00:23:08,881 --> 00:23:10,593
Ah, my nerves.

626
00:23:10,593 --> 00:23:12,350
We're all on edge right now.

627
00:23:12,350 --> 00:23:14,593
[But I'm the worst]

628
00:23:14,593 --> 00:23:16,118
[Sneak peek]

629
00:23:16,118 --> 00:23:17,992
[Frozen]
Come on.

630
00:23:17,992 --> 00:23:20,059
Let's see, hold on a sec.

631
00:23:20,059 --> 00:23:22,292
[What is it that's got him like that?]
No way.

632
00:23:23,326 --> 00:23:25,827
[Sigh]
No way.

633
00:23:25,827 --> 00:23:28,492
[A subtle mix of smile and sigh]
No way! Park Seo Jun.

634
00:23:28,492 --> 00:23:30,193
- No way.
- Come on, you're not that kind of guy.

635
00:23:30,193 --> 00:23:31,792
[A phone hat trick, surely not?]
The corners of his mouth keep creeping up.

636
00:23:31,792 --> 00:23:33,744
[So what's the third benefit?]
They keep creeping up.

637
00:23:33,744 --> 00:23:36,332
[Lodging won!]
Honestly.

638
00:23:36,332 --> 00:23:37,308
Just that alone.

639
00:23:37,308 --> 00:23:40,026
[A weirdly mixed reaction from the trio]

640
00:23:40,026 --> 00:23:42,693
There was just something I really wanted.

641
00:23:42,693 --> 00:23:45,591
I had something I was really hoping for,
that's why.

642
00:23:45,591 --> 00:23:47,827
There was something I was really set on,

643
00:23:47,827 --> 00:23:51,294
and not getting that is
what made it feel a little off.

644
00:23:51,294 --> 00:23:53,524
Honestly, lodging is great too,

645
00:23:53,524 --> 00:23:55,526
but the number-one thing I kept hoping for...

646
00:23:55,526 --> 00:23:57,326
was the car, to be honest.

647
00:23:57,326 --> 00:24:02,494
The minute the car drops,
our travel route really comes together,

648
00:24:03,401 --> 00:24:06,504
so it stings a little, but still,

649
00:24:06,504 --> 00:24:07,995
lodging works out fine.

650
00:24:07,995 --> 00:24:10,321
It's a way to save us some money.

651
00:24:10,321 --> 00:24:12,300
[Better than the phone, we'll take it]

652
00:24:12,300 --> 00:24:15,059
Honestly, lodging's all right.

653
00:24:15,059 --> 00:24:16,395
Anyway, nice job, everyone.

654
00:24:16,395 --> 00:24:17,916
Congrats on the lodging.

655
00:24:17,916 --> 00:24:19,154
[Cheers, phone dodged! Lodging acquired]

656
00:24:19,154 --> 00:24:22,860
So if you pick your destination,

657
00:24:22,860 --> 00:24:24,827
we'll book you the kind of place

658
00:24:24,827 --> 00:24:27,755
at that destination that you're after.

659
00:24:27,755 --> 00:24:29,874
Oh man, we haven't decided that.

660
00:24:29,874 --> 00:24:32,482
That's because we were...

661
00:24:32,482 --> 00:24:34,534
assuming the car was a lock.

662
00:24:34,534 --> 00:24:36,954
[With a car, Yeongdeok. Without, no plan]
So the car was the only thing on your minds.

663
00:24:36,954 --> 00:24:39,154
[Fidget]
We didn't sort that out.

664
00:24:39,154 --> 00:24:41,906
We were talking about activities, weren't we?

665
00:24:41,906 --> 00:24:43,927
[Woo Shik pulls a notebook out of her bag]

666
00:24:43,927 --> 00:24:45,514
It's been a while since this map came out.

667
00:24:45,514 --> 00:24:47,645
Woo Shik's giving off
a real mastermind vibe right now.

668
00:24:47,645 --> 00:24:49,981
[Dazzling]

669
00:24:49,981 --> 00:24:52,111
[Trying to decide by checking
the map in the notebook]

670
00:24:52,111 --> 00:24:53,751
- So we're right here.
- Right.

671
00:24:53,751 --> 00:24:56,186
[Dead serious]

672
00:24:57,560 --> 00:25:00,051
[Zero clue where or how to go]
I'm drawing a complete blank.

673
00:25:00,051 --> 00:25:04,191
In Gyeongju, that... World place,
somebody recommended it...

674
00:25:04,191 --> 00:25:06,364
- Gyeongju World?
- Yeah.

675
00:25:06,364 --> 00:25:08,302
But it's going to be night
by the time we get there, right?

676
00:25:08,302 --> 00:25:10,008
What time is it?

677
00:25:10,008 --> 00:25:11,192
[Current time: 11:15 AM]
11.

678
00:25:11,192 --> 00:25:15,006
Without a phone, there's no way
to tell how long Gyeongju takes.

679
00:25:15,006 --> 00:25:15,983
Just like that.

680
00:25:15,983 --> 00:25:17,626
- Beats me, just like that.
- Just like that.

681
00:25:17,626 --> 00:25:19,777
So getting to Gyeongju right now...

682
00:25:19,777 --> 00:25:22,706
- Oh, we don't even know what to take.
- No clue.

683
00:25:22,706 --> 00:25:25,026
[Familiar]
We'll probably have to transfer somewhere.

684
00:25:25,026 --> 00:25:26,393
- Chungcheong-do and Jeolla-do.
- Daegu.

685
00:25:26,393 --> 00:25:28,793
[Backtracking]
We'd be heading back toward Daegu again.

686
00:25:28,793 --> 00:25:30,159
The efficiency is just awful.

687
00:25:30,159 --> 00:25:32,923
[Backtracking Boseong to Gyeongju: five hours]
Yeah, exactly.

688
00:25:33,825 --> 00:25:36,394
Anything around Gwangju over here?

689
00:25:36,394 --> 00:25:38,660
Gwangju works too.

690
00:25:38,660 --> 00:25:41,413
- Should we head to Gwangju?
- Should we head to Gwangju?

691
00:25:41,413 --> 00:25:42,867
How about somewhere close?

692
00:25:42,867 --> 00:25:45,588
[Boseong to Gwangju is 1 hour and 30 min away!]

693
00:25:45,588 --> 00:25:49,193
From Gwangju, we could swing by Gongju,
where you want to go.

694
00:25:49,193 --> 00:25:50,568
- That works too.
- Right.

695
00:25:50,568 --> 00:25:52,189
The top places I want to hit

696
00:25:52,189 --> 00:25:54,289
were Gongju, Yeongdeok, and Samcheok.

697
00:25:54,289 --> 00:25:56,347
Because you're a princess?

698
00:25:56,347 --> 00:25:57,715
[Caught off guard]

699
00:25:57,715 --> 00:26:00,418
[Hahaha]

700
00:26:00,418 --> 00:26:02,687
[Let's all share a laugh]

701
00:26:02,687 --> 00:26:03,554
So, Gwangju for us?

702
00:26:03,554 --> 00:26:04,822
- Gwangju!
- Let's go!

703
00:26:04,822 --> 00:26:06,049
- Go.
- Gwangju, are we good?

704
00:26:06,049 --> 00:26:07,593
- All good.
- Let's hit Mudeungsan Mountain.

705
00:26:07,593 --> 00:26:09,689
[Heading off to Gwangju]
- Let's go. - Are we doing a hike?

706
00:26:09,689 --> 00:26:11,229
Alright, first stop is the terminal, right?

707
00:26:11,229 --> 00:26:13,493
I think we can head
to where we caught the bus yesterday.

708
00:26:13,493 --> 00:26:14,579
Sounds good.

709
00:26:14,579 --> 00:26:16,060
By the way, can I actually ask?

710
00:26:16,060 --> 00:26:16,700
- About what?
- About what?

711
00:26:16,700 --> 00:26:19,370
[Want to confirm how to get to Gwangju]
We're heading to Gwangju...

712
00:26:19,370 --> 00:26:21,806
so should we just check on how to get there?

713
00:26:21,806 --> 00:26:23,641
- Gwangju from here?
- Right.

714
00:26:23,641 --> 00:26:26,711
[Decided to ask the guesthouse owner!]

715
00:26:26,711 --> 00:26:27,879
[Peeking in]

716
00:26:27,879 --> 00:26:29,547
We're heading out now.

717
00:26:29,547 --> 00:26:30,848
Yes.

718
00:26:30,848 --> 00:26:32,560
So we're thinking of heading to Gwangju

719
00:26:32,560 --> 00:26:34,340
and we were wondering how to...

720
00:26:34,340 --> 00:26:35,999
Are you taking the bus?

721
00:26:35,999 --> 00:26:38,620
Are buses and trains both options?

722
00:26:38,620 --> 00:26:43,426
There's a train,
but if you go to the mart here...

723
00:26:43,426 --> 00:26:45,241
there's a direct bus
that runs to Sotae Station,

724
00:26:45,241 --> 00:26:47,131
Hakdong, and the terminal in Gwangju.

725
00:26:47,131 --> 00:26:47,997
Really?

726
00:26:47,997 --> 00:26:50,756
[Direct news straight to them]
Runs several times a day.

727
00:26:50,756 --> 00:26:53,756
- The mart at the three-way is the stop.
- Okay.

728
00:26:53,756 --> 00:26:58,359
So as for what's next,
you've got the 12:20 one.

729
00:26:58,359 --> 00:27:00,257
We can grab breakfast until then.

730
00:27:00,257 --> 00:27:01,291
Got it.

731
00:27:01,291 --> 00:27:02,817
[Waiting over brunch]
Thanks so much.

732
00:27:02,817 --> 00:27:04,631
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

733
00:27:04,631 --> 00:27:05,850
Take care of your health.

734
00:27:05,850 --> 00:27:06,831
- Thanks again.
- I'd love to know your names.

735
00:27:06,831 --> 00:27:07,972
Jung Yumi.

736
00:27:07,972 --> 00:27:09,232
I'm Jung Yumi.

737
00:27:09,232 --> 00:27:10,432
Choi Woo Shik.

738
00:27:10,432 --> 00:27:12,712
- I'm Park Seo Jun.
- I know you already.

739
00:27:12,712 --> 00:27:14,760
You know me? Thank you.

740
00:27:14,760 --> 00:27:16,460
He's lucky.

741
00:27:16,460 --> 00:27:19,792
When would I ever have celebrities
show up at my place, really?

742
00:27:19,792 --> 00:27:21,599
Jung Yumi.

743
00:27:21,599 --> 00:27:24,502
[Owner wants to write it down to remember]
Choi Woo Shik.

744
00:27:24,502 --> 00:27:26,293
- I see you a lot on TV.
- Right.

745
00:27:26,293 --> 00:27:27,939
- Park...
- Park Seo Jun.

746
00:27:27,939 --> 00:27:29,481
Park Seo Jun.

747
00:27:29,481 --> 00:27:31,109
[Park Seo Jun she knows for sure]
- And he's... - Park Seo Jun's famous.

748
00:27:31,109 --> 00:27:32,343
[Shy]

749
00:27:32,343 --> 00:27:34,679
- Got it, thanks.
- Thank you.

750
00:27:34,679 --> 00:27:36,726
[Cozy stay plus a Gwangju travel tip, thanks!]
- Thank you. - Thank you.

751
00:27:36,726 --> 00:27:38,193
You all did great.

752
00:27:38,193 --> 00:27:41,170
- Take care now.
- Yeah.

753
00:27:41,170 --> 00:27:42,671
At least it wasn't the phone, what a relief.

754
00:27:42,671 --> 00:27:43,726
- Such a relief.
- Yeah.

755
00:27:43,726 --> 00:27:46,891
[No phone meant good intel from the owner]
So glad, that would've been the worst.

756
00:27:46,891 --> 00:27:49,251
But first we should figure out
where the *rin mart is.

757
00:27:49,251 --> 00:27:51,829
There it is. Right out front.

758
00:27:51,829 --> 00:27:53,626
[The mart is a 4-min walk from the guesthouse]
Whoa, that's awesome.

759
00:27:53,626 --> 00:27:56,959
- Alright.
- Gwang* Express stop.

760
00:27:56,959 --> 00:27:59,737
Can we buy tickets right there?

761
00:27:59,737 --> 00:28:02,664
[Looks like your run-of-the-mill mart]

762
00:28:02,664 --> 00:28:04,185
So we buy them here?

763
00:28:04,185 --> 00:28:05,305
Yeah, she told us to buy them here.

764
00:28:05,305 --> 00:28:06,377
Found it.

765
00:28:06,377 --> 00:28:08,223
[Looks like they spotted something]

766
00:28:08,223 --> 00:28:09,564
[Bus schedule]
- Gwangju. - This one?

767
00:28:09,564 --> 00:28:12,204
12:20 on the dot, she was right.

768
00:28:12,204 --> 00:28:13,965
Looks like it stops by the tea fields,
then continues on.

769
00:28:13,965 --> 00:28:17,164
- Then Hakdong, then on to Gwangju.
- Right.

770
00:28:17,164 --> 00:28:18,665
- Looking good.
- Yeah, not bad.

771
00:28:18,665 --> 00:28:21,792
- Should we head in?
- Let's first ask how many hours it takes.

772
00:28:21,792 --> 00:28:23,504
[Stepping into the mart!]
Hello.

773
00:28:23,504 --> 00:28:27,005
Hi, we'd like to buy tickets to Gwangju.

774
00:28:27,005 --> 00:28:29,159
- The 12:20 one.
- Sure.

775
00:28:29,159 --> 00:28:31,665
A lot of people seem
to head to Gwangju from here.

776
00:28:31,665 --> 00:28:33,171
It takes an hour and a half from here.

777
00:28:33,171 --> 00:28:34,927
[Pretty close!]
- Perfect. - Quick...

778
00:28:34,927 --> 00:28:37,705
It's a direct route.
Just stops at Boseong, then straight there.

779
00:28:37,705 --> 00:28:39,745
- Oh, nice, nice.
- It's a deluxe bus.

780
00:28:39,745 --> 00:28:41,078
- It's a deluxe bus?
- Yes.

781
00:28:41,078 --> 00:28:42,113
Oh, not bad.

782
00:28:42,113 --> 00:28:43,244
How much?

783
00:28:43,244 --> 00:28:44,865
[Per person]
14,400 won.

784
00:28:44,865 --> 00:28:46,293
- Let's grab them.
- And the 42,000 won cost

785
00:28:46,293 --> 00:28:48,305
works out perfectly for us.

786
00:28:48,305 --> 00:28:49,860
- Direct ride, and lodging's covered too.
- Right.

787
00:28:49,860 --> 00:28:51,245
Since lodging's already sorted.

788
00:28:51,245 --> 00:28:52,857
[Make it happen]
- Alright. - Alright.

789
00:28:52,857 --> 00:28:55,359
[Three seats are booked on the spot]

790
00:28:55,359 --> 00:28:57,626
That'll be 43,200 won.

791
00:28:57,626 --> 00:29:00,097
- You got 200 won?
- I've got 200 won.

792
00:29:00,097 --> 00:29:01,999
[Putting every last coin to good use]

793
00:29:01,999 --> 00:29:03,359
[Fresh tickets roll out]

794
00:29:03,359 --> 00:29:04,575
Got it.

795
00:29:04,575 --> 00:29:07,075
Here's 50,200 won.

796
00:29:07,075 --> 00:29:09,015
- Just give back 7,000 won.
- Yes.

797
00:29:09,015 --> 00:29:10,336
[Gwangju bus fare: -43,200 won]
- 12:20. - Yeah.

798
00:29:10,336 --> 00:29:11,675
[Balance: 269,010 won]
- Thank you. - When the bus comes,

799
00:29:11,675 --> 00:29:14,854
- it pulls up here and leaves from here.
- Got it.

800
00:29:14,854 --> 00:29:16,013
- Thanks so much.
- Sure.

801
00:29:16,013 --> 00:29:18,795
- Alright, let's hurry and grab a bite.
- Let's eat.

802
00:29:18,795 --> 00:29:21,875
Should we go back to that gimbap place?
Where to?

803
00:29:21,875 --> 00:29:22,936
- How about that snack spot?
- Yeah, let's do it.

804
00:29:22,936 --> 00:29:26,356
What about that green-pork specialty place?
It's got a vibe, right?

805
00:29:26,356 --> 00:29:29,026
Hey, they've also got
green tea soybean paste stew there.

806
00:29:29,026 --> 00:29:32,255
- Nice.
- Yeah, you can't find that anywhere else.

807
00:29:32,255 --> 00:29:33,296
Are they open?

808
00:29:33,296 --> 00:29:35,235
Looks like they're open.

809
00:29:35,235 --> 00:29:38,255
- "Breakfast served." Should we eat here?
- Yeah, let's do it.

810
00:29:38,255 --> 00:29:39,612
Hello.

811
00:29:39,612 --> 00:29:41,416
- Welcome in.
- We were hoping to have a meal.

812
00:29:41,416 --> 00:29:43,874
- Are you serving food?
- Yes.

813
00:29:43,874 --> 00:29:45,443
[They settle in at a table]

814
00:29:45,443 --> 00:29:47,035
So what do we order?

815
00:29:47,035 --> 00:29:48,613
- Should we go three soybean stews?
- Let's get three soybean stews.

816
00:29:48,613 --> 00:29:50,081
Three orders of soybean paste stew, please.

817
00:29:50,081 --> 00:29:51,254
[Total: 30,000 won]
Got it.

818
00:29:51,254 --> 00:29:53,684
So at this point, we have...

819
00:29:53,684 --> 00:29:56,554
After we spend 30,000 won,

820
00:29:56,554 --> 00:29:57,521
how much will be left?

821
00:29:57,521 --> 00:29:59,508
We have to burn through all of this today.

822
00:29:59,508 --> 00:30:00,625
[A happy dilemma like none before]

823
00:30:00,625 --> 00:30:03,288
- Lunch, dinner.
- Lunch is taken care of for now.

824
00:30:03,288 --> 00:30:06,718
Transportation... even if it costs
another 20,000 won.

825
00:30:06,718 --> 00:30:08,848
[The bills are practically
fluttering around...]

826
00:30:08,848 --> 00:30:10,128
Let's go to the Songjeong-ri bakery.

827
00:30:10,128 --> 00:30:11,600
- Huh?
- The Songjeong-ri bakery.

828
00:30:11,600 --> 00:30:14,471
Oh, the bakery. So even if we spend
30,000 won at the bakery...

829
00:30:14,471 --> 00:30:16,376
[Still rolling in luxury vibes]

830
00:30:16,376 --> 00:30:19,148
Or should we seriously do
a day trip to Jeju Island?

831
00:30:19,148 --> 00:30:21,020
- We can go from Gwangju.
- If we still have a lot of money left...

832
00:30:21,020 --> 00:30:22,991
We can go from Gwangju, from Gwangju Airport.

833
00:30:22,991 --> 00:30:24,686
I'm in.

834
00:30:24,686 --> 00:30:28,264
And we can just ask them to book us
a place in Jeju since it's expensive there.

835
00:30:28,264 --> 00:30:30,415
- Today?
- Yeah.

836
00:30:30,415 --> 00:30:33,062
[Assessing the situation]
Gwangju tonight?

837
00:30:33,062 --> 00:30:36,735
We go to Gwangju now
and then head straight to Jeju.

838
00:30:36,735 --> 00:30:38,420
We want to go to Jeju today.

839
00:30:38,420 --> 00:30:41,207
And then they can just book us a place in Jeju.

840
00:30:41,207 --> 00:30:42,575
[Will this actually be okay?]

841
00:30:42,575 --> 00:30:44,770
[Hahahahaha]

842
00:30:44,770 --> 00:30:45,825
Well, I mean...

843
00:30:45,825 --> 00:30:47,833
We don't know how much the plane tickets cost.

844
00:30:47,833 --> 00:30:49,562
Yeah, as long as you can get the tickets.

845
00:30:49,562 --> 00:30:51,269
J** Air flights are like 30,000 won.

846
00:30:51,269 --> 00:30:54,309
From Gimpo it's like 60,000 won and stuff.

847
00:30:54,309 --> 00:30:55,343
There are even cheaper ones.

848
00:30:55,343 --> 00:30:56,829
Yeah, 40,000 won, 30,000 won.

849
00:30:56,829 --> 00:30:58,762
[They even know the market prices]
- It'll definitely be cheap. - Yeah.

850
00:30:58,762 --> 00:31:00,951
[Notebook appears]

851
00:31:00,951 --> 00:31:03,543
[A map now more familiar than their phones]

852
00:31:03,543 --> 00:31:06,706
- Gwangju International Airport?
- Yeah, this one's big.

853
00:31:06,706 --> 00:31:09,206
- There are lots of activities in Jeju too.
- Exactly.

854
00:31:09,206 --> 00:31:10,596
I want to ride a buggy there.

855
00:31:10,596 --> 00:31:13,092
[Desires bursting out]
- What? What's that? - Oh, a buggy?

856
00:31:13,092 --> 00:31:15,684
There are buggies, and you can hike
Hallasan Mountain too.

857
00:31:15,684 --> 00:31:18,042
[The more they talk, the more hyped they get]
There are tons of activities.

858
00:31:18,042 --> 00:31:19,416
- Or what about renting one
- Yeah.

859
00:31:19,416 --> 00:31:20,874
and doing a motorcycle trip?

860
00:31:20,874 --> 00:31:23,160
- Scooter? That'd be amazing.
- I can't ride a scooter.

861
00:31:23,160 --> 00:31:24,675
Yumi, you can just ride behind me.

862
00:31:24,675 --> 00:31:25,763
Hey, hop on!

863
00:31:25,763 --> 00:31:27,442
[Vroom]

864
00:31:27,442 --> 00:31:28,558
[That's one way to do it...]

865
00:31:28,558 --> 00:31:29,554
Sounds good.

866
00:31:29,554 --> 00:31:31,404
- Safely.
- Anything is fine.

867
00:31:31,404 --> 00:31:32,495
I'm good with it, I...

868
00:31:32,495 --> 00:31:34,864
Ah, I've always wanted to try that,
like along the beach.

869
00:31:34,864 --> 00:31:36,130
Let's go, let's go!

870
00:31:36,130 --> 00:31:38,269
[Already driving through Jeju in their minds]
Wow, that'd be amazing.

871
00:31:38,269 --> 00:31:40,137
And we could do farm experiences too.

872
00:31:40,137 --> 00:31:41,577
- Tangerine farm experience.
- Picking tangerines.

873
00:31:41,577 --> 00:31:43,866
- We could even make money there.
- By picking tangerines?

874
00:31:43,866 --> 00:31:46,657
- Pick tangerines and bring them back with us.
- Right!

875
00:31:46,657 --> 00:31:49,033
Yeah, and then during the livestream
we can hold up tangerines like this.

876
00:31:49,033 --> 00:31:50,512
[Welcome to Jeju]

877
00:31:50,512 --> 00:31:53,880
[Their dream Jeju workcation is complete]
We brought it from Jeju.

878
00:31:53,880 --> 00:31:56,013
Ah, I think this is
enough reason to go to Jeju.

879
00:31:56,013 --> 00:31:57,521
- Totally enough.
- Then let's go to Jeju.

880
00:31:57,521 --> 00:32:00,599
- Should we go to Jeju?
- Let's go, let's go!

881
00:32:00,599 --> 00:32:03,526
Then our destination is
Gwangju International Airport now, right?

882
00:32:03,526 --> 00:32:05,015
Yep.

883
00:32:05,015 --> 00:32:07,473
[Fully embracing spontaneous travel...]
Sounds good.

884
00:32:07,473 --> 00:32:09,286
The production crew is freaking out right now.

885
00:32:09,286 --> 00:32:11,391
We're not booking a place in Gwangju for now.

886
00:32:11,391 --> 00:32:14,954
- Please don't book us a place in Gwangju.
- Don't book it for now. And...

887
00:32:14,954 --> 00:32:16,127
- There'll be flights.
- Yeah.

888
00:32:16,127 --> 00:32:17,966
[The room is overflowing
with baseless confidence]

889
00:32:17,966 --> 00:32:19,628
- Sleep in Jeju tonight,
- Yeah.

890
00:32:19,628 --> 00:32:23,334
and then take a plane
to Yangyang International Airport.

891
00:32:23,334 --> 00:32:24,473
[Out of control]
Ah, nice.

892
00:32:24,473 --> 00:32:26,589
- Sounds good, right?
- I'm in. I approve.

893
00:32:26,589 --> 00:32:28,013
- Nice, nice.
- I approve.

894
00:32:28,013 --> 00:32:30,020
We're going
from Yangyang International Airport.

895
00:32:30,020 --> 00:32:32,102
[Who knows how far this Jeju trip buzz will go]
- Nice, nice. - Nice. That sounds good too.

896
00:32:33,144 --> 00:32:35,211
This is crazy.

897
00:32:35,211 --> 00:32:37,100
[Just as things start getting overwhelming,
the side dishes arrive...]

898
00:32:37,100 --> 00:32:38,308
- Oh, seasoned cockles!
- Oh, here come the cockles.

899
00:32:38,308 --> 00:32:40,640
Ah, this is what we wanted to eat.

900
00:32:40,640 --> 00:32:41,827
[And now, the star of the meal arrives]

901
00:32:41,827 --> 00:32:43,893
- Wow...
- Wow!

902
00:32:45,253 --> 00:32:47,899
[Introducing a hearty
nine-sided dish made with care]

903
00:32:47,899 --> 00:32:51,975
[The savory lineup led by vegetables
and pancakes is on the right]

904
00:32:53,260 --> 00:32:58,427
[While the refreshing lineup led by seaweed
and cockles is set on the left!]

905
00:33:00,137 --> 00:33:03,840
[And today's main dish:
green tea soybean paste stew]

906
00:33:03,840 --> 00:33:08,500
[Tofu, mushrooms, and rich soybean paste stew
with a subtle green tea scent...]

907
00:33:08,500 --> 00:33:11,390
[And there was another hidden star...]

908
00:33:11,390 --> 00:33:13,336
[Refreshing clams]

909
00:33:14,696 --> 00:33:18,242
[We'll eat well before heading out]

910
00:33:18,242 --> 00:33:21,153
- Looks like we can eat right away?
- Yep, it's boiling hot.

911
00:33:21,153 --> 00:33:24,783
[The first bowl, full of soft tofu]

912
00:33:24,783 --> 00:33:27,113
[Goes straight to big sis]
- Lady first. - Thank you!

913
00:33:27,843 --> 00:33:30,301
[As he immediately scoops the second bowl...]

914
00:33:30,301 --> 00:33:32,873
Wow, the mushrooms...

915
00:33:32,873 --> 00:33:36,382
[Can't resist, first bite
with cockles on white rice]

916
00:33:39,250 --> 00:33:40,555
Try this quickly. Oh...

917
00:33:40,555 --> 00:33:43,072
- Is this what you wanted?
- Yeah.

918
00:33:43,072 --> 00:33:44,582
Thank you for the meal!

919
00:33:44,582 --> 00:33:47,072
[Seo Jun tries the broth first]

920
00:33:47,072 --> 00:33:50,088
Whoa, darn. Whoa.

921
00:33:50,088 --> 00:33:51,690
[Immediately goes back for more]

922
00:33:51,690 --> 00:33:53,952
[Hits the spot]
Oh man.

923
00:33:53,952 --> 00:33:56,695
[Woo Shik follows Seo Jun
and takes a sip of the broth too]

924
00:33:56,695 --> 00:33:58,545
Ah, that's good.

925
00:33:58,545 --> 00:34:00,826
[Po-po starts with the soft tofu first!]

926
00:34:01,968 --> 00:34:04,382
- Yum!
- Oh, wow...

927
00:34:04,382 --> 00:34:06,879
- This?
- Yeah.

928
00:34:06,879 --> 00:34:09,476
[Now it's Woo Shik's recommended cockle time]

929
00:34:11,055 --> 00:34:12,507
- Oh, this is so delicious.
- Yeah?

930
00:34:12,507 --> 00:34:14,205
[This goes in too]

931
00:34:14,205 --> 00:34:16,131
So delicious...

932
00:34:17,059 --> 00:34:23,059
[Everyone is falling
into an endless broth loop...]

933
00:34:24,190 --> 00:34:25,997
[Suddenly, pancakes enter the scene]
- Oh! - Oh my gosh.

934
00:34:25,997 --> 00:34:27,376
What kind of pancake is it?

935
00:34:27,376 --> 00:34:29,091
- Mugwort pancake.
- Mugwort pancake? Oh my.

936
00:34:29,091 --> 00:34:30,511
- Thank you.
- Oh, thank you.

937
00:34:30,511 --> 00:34:31,852
- Wow.
- Oh, my!

938
00:34:31,852 --> 00:34:35,065
[Tearing apart the glossy,
glistening mugwort pancake]

939
00:34:35,065 --> 00:34:36,834
[And taking a bite right away...]

940
00:34:36,834 --> 00:34:38,771
[Frowning in delicious concentration]

941
00:34:38,771 --> 00:34:41,151
[Woo Shik takes a huge bite too]

942
00:34:41,151 --> 00:34:43,275
- It's my first time trying mugwort pancake.
- Oh, really?

943
00:34:43,275 --> 00:34:45,336
[Po-po takes a fragrant bite too]
- It's delicious. - Yeah.

944
00:34:46,535 --> 00:34:49,562
[Meanwhile, someone next to them
is totally absorbed in the mugwort pancake]

945
00:34:51,424 --> 00:34:55,177
[Yumi slides more mugwort pancake
over to Woo Shik, who's eating well]

946
00:34:55,177 --> 00:34:58,510
I never thought we'd get to eat
such a warm meal this morning.

947
00:34:58,510 --> 00:35:00,824
- Feels like it's been a long time.
- Yeah.

948
00:35:01,685 --> 00:35:03,268
[Cough]
Exactly...

949
00:35:03,268 --> 00:35:07,752
See? As long as we don't have our phones,
everything's perfect.

950
00:35:07,752 --> 00:35:11,718
[Everything's perfect... right?]

951
00:35:11,718 --> 00:35:13,118
[Ding ding]

952
00:35:13,118 --> 00:35:15,493
[Meanwhile, there was one group
for whom things were definitely not okay...]

953
00:35:15,493 --> 00:35:17,540
[Ding ding]
- They're in chaos. - Huh?

954
00:35:17,540 --> 00:35:20,380
- They immediately started a meeting.
- Oh gosh, what do they do?

955
00:35:20,380 --> 00:35:22,846
It's chaos over there right now.

956
00:35:23,623 --> 00:35:25,695
- One night...
- This is driving me crazy.

957
00:35:25,695 --> 00:35:27,268
[Production crew enters emergency meeting mode]

958
00:35:28,970 --> 00:35:33,237
Honestly, I think they're suffering more
from this trip than we are.

959
00:35:33,237 --> 00:35:35,742
[Well, we are all tied together
by fate after all...]

960
00:35:35,742 --> 00:35:38,865
But seriously, if we go to Jeju,

961
00:35:38,865 --> 00:35:41,565
what about their plane tickets?

962
00:35:41,565 --> 00:35:43,376
- Good point.
- It'll work out somehow.

963
00:35:43,376 --> 00:35:46,057
But if it's impossible, let us know in advance.

964
00:35:46,057 --> 00:35:48,478
Because we're going either way.

965
00:35:48,478 --> 00:35:50,777
We've got our camcorder anyway.

966
00:35:50,777 --> 00:35:51,944
[So... reassuring]

967
00:35:51,944 --> 00:35:53,565
- Please take good care of it.
- Yeah.

968
00:35:53,565 --> 00:35:54,618
We'll film it somehow.

969
00:35:54,618 --> 00:35:56,568
[Jung Yumi, Seoul Institute
of the Arts film major graduate]

970
00:35:56,568 --> 00:35:57,878
- Want more rice?
- Yeah.

971
00:35:57,878 --> 00:35:58,906
You eat this.

972
00:35:58,906 --> 00:36:01,186
- I can't finish it all.
- Yumi, you eat more.

973
00:36:01,186 --> 00:36:04,572
[In that case... he takes a big bite]

974
00:36:04,572 --> 00:36:07,732
[Woo Shik's appetite exploded today]

975
00:36:07,732 --> 00:36:10,042
[Staring intently]

976
00:36:10,042 --> 00:36:12,048
Is this water for us?

977
00:36:12,048 --> 00:36:14,546
[Passing the water around]
- Is this green tea? - Oh, it is green tea.

978
00:36:14,546 --> 00:36:16,415
This is green tea!

979
00:36:16,415 --> 00:36:18,950
I guess they even serve
green tea as water here.

980
00:36:18,950 --> 00:36:20,266
Looks like it.

981
00:36:20,266 --> 00:36:22,995
Only possible because it's Boseong.

982
00:36:22,995 --> 00:36:24,630
[Gulp gulp]

983
00:36:24,630 --> 00:36:27,173
[Refreshing their mouths with green tea water]

984
00:36:27,173 --> 00:36:28,932
You finished all.

985
00:36:29,966 --> 00:36:32,646
[The trio even cleared all the side dishes]

986
00:36:32,646 --> 00:36:36,128
We just had soybean paste stew for brunch.

987
00:36:36,128 --> 00:36:37,927
- Oh, it's 12:15.
- Let's go.

988
00:36:37,927 --> 00:36:40,014
[Before they know it,
the bus arrives in five minutes]

989
00:36:40,014 --> 00:36:41,941
- Oh my.
- I saw you on TV.

990
00:36:41,941 --> 00:36:45,974
- There are only two, so you'll have to share.
- Ah, yes, thank you.

991
00:36:45,974 --> 00:36:47,094
Sweet potatoes.

992
00:36:47,094 --> 00:36:48,514
[Happiness]

993
00:36:48,514 --> 00:36:50,462
- Thank you for the meal.
- Thank you for the meal.

994
00:36:50,462 --> 00:36:52,161
Goodbye.

995
00:36:52,161 --> 00:36:54,314
[Expense report: breakfast -30,000 won,
Remaining balance: 239,010 won]

996
00:36:54,314 --> 00:36:56,708
[Heading to the bus stop right in front]
Wow!

997
00:36:56,708 --> 00:36:58,909
- Let's sit over there.
- Oh, is there a seat?

998
00:36:58,909 --> 00:37:01,507
[They arrive in 30 seconds
and take a short break]

999
00:37:01,507 --> 00:37:03,665
- Oh, that's ours.
- It's here!

1000
00:37:03,665 --> 00:37:06,825
[Right on cue... the bus arrives]
- We'll get going now. - We're off.

1001
00:37:06,825 --> 00:37:08,058
Let's ask. Ask them.

1002
00:37:08,058 --> 00:37:10,626
- Well, this bus is going to Gwangju, right?
- Yes.

1003
00:37:10,626 --> 00:37:12,982
[Successfully boarded the bus to Gwangju!]

1004
00:37:13,852 --> 00:37:15,592
Wow, this is nice.

1005
00:37:15,592 --> 00:37:18,270
[The premium bus is totally Yumi's style]
I'm sitting at the end today.

1006
00:37:18,270 --> 00:37:23,016
[Set down the backpack and take a seat]

1007
00:37:23,016 --> 00:37:25,137
[Slide]

1008
00:37:25,137 --> 00:37:28,621
- Bye, Boseong!
- Bye.

1009
00:37:28,621 --> 00:37:29,728
We're off!

1010
00:37:29,728 --> 00:37:31,175
[Saying their goodbyes]

1011
00:37:32,072 --> 00:37:34,255
[Expected travel time: 1 hour 30 minutes
from Boseong to Gwangju]

1012
00:37:35,086 --> 00:37:36,179
Anyone want a chewy candy?

1013
00:37:36,179 --> 00:37:37,840
- Me!
- Me!

1014
00:37:37,840 --> 00:37:40,559
[Then take it out]

1015
00:37:40,559 --> 00:37:42,093
- Where? It's here, right?
- Yeah.

1016
00:37:42,093 --> 00:37:44,733
[Their telepathy is too strong]
- Where is it? - There, hand it to me.

1017
00:37:44,733 --> 00:37:47,146
[Snack bundle]

1018
00:37:47,146 --> 00:37:48,626
Grape flavor or strawberry flavor?

1019
00:37:48,626 --> 00:37:50,315
- Strawberry.
- I want strawberry.

1020
00:37:50,315 --> 00:37:51,923
[Their telepathy works perfectly]

1021
00:37:51,923 --> 00:37:54,477
- We should give one to each person.
- Yeah.

1022
00:37:55,332 --> 00:37:57,359
Two, three, four, five, six...

1023
00:37:57,359 --> 00:37:58,891
Six of them.

1024
00:38:00,450 --> 00:38:01,537
[Pouring out]

1025
00:38:01,537 --> 00:38:02,767
Oh...

1026
00:38:03,392 --> 00:38:05,733
[Picking them all up neatly]

1027
00:38:05,733 --> 00:38:08,299
[Casually tosses it over]
Huh? Thank you.

1028
00:38:09,486 --> 00:38:11,438
[One goes straight into his mouth too]

1029
00:38:11,438 --> 00:38:16,404
[Woo Shik munches away after sharing]

1030
00:38:16,404 --> 00:38:20,841
[Chewy candy tastes best when shared]

1031
00:38:20,841 --> 00:38:24,323
She said there were only two sweet potatoes,
so she could only give us two.

1032
00:38:24,323 --> 00:38:26,410
Sweet potatoes? Oh, that's more than enough.

1033
00:38:26,410 --> 00:38:27,717
Yeah, that surprised me.

1034
00:38:27,717 --> 00:38:31,797
Everywhere we go, food just keeps appearing.

1035
00:38:31,797 --> 00:38:33,943
Guess we're blessed with food luck.

1036
00:38:34,550 --> 00:38:35,958
Honestly, I think we have enough snacks.

1037
00:38:35,958 --> 00:38:37,304
[Looking back at "The Trio's Food Luck" series]

1038
00:38:37,304 --> 00:38:39,017
[1. Dubai Chewy Cookie from the passenger]
Oh, thank you!

1039
00:38:39,017 --> 00:38:41,003
[2. Bread from the elderly gentleman]
- Oh, my. - Oh, my!

1040
00:38:41,003 --> 00:38:43,018
[3. Chewy candy from the girls]

1041
00:38:43,018 --> 00:38:44,843
[4. Sweet potatoes from the owner]
Ah, yes, thank you!

1042
00:38:44,843 --> 00:38:46,075
[Eyes open wide]

1043
00:38:46,075 --> 00:38:49,000
The sleeves are getting dirtier and dirtier.

1044
00:38:49,000 --> 00:38:50,907
[Seo Jun stares at it too]

1045
00:38:50,907 --> 00:38:53,838
Seriously, I think I can
stop wearing this outfit now.

1046
00:38:53,838 --> 00:38:55,954
- Ah, you mean forever?
- Yeah.

1047
00:38:55,954 --> 00:38:57,462
Forever.

1048
00:38:58,304 --> 00:39:00,846
Even my shoes turned yellow.

1049
00:39:00,846 --> 00:39:04,232
[Feeling the traces of the past four days]

1050
00:39:04,232 --> 00:39:06,939
[Maybe their appearance just attracts food...]

1051
00:39:06,939 --> 00:39:08,788
[Passed out from the smell]

1052
00:39:08,788 --> 00:39:10,860
Should we seriously buy some fabric refresher?

1053
00:39:10,860 --> 00:39:12,981
- A fabric refresher.
- Yeah.

1054
00:39:12,981 --> 00:39:14,621
It'd be nice to have a small one.

1055
00:39:14,621 --> 00:39:16,738
- Do convenience stores sell small ones?
- Yeah.

1056
00:39:16,738 --> 00:39:17,947
Oh, really?

1057
00:39:17,947 --> 00:39:22,374
But, if we go to a laundromat,
we won't need it.

1058
00:39:22,374 --> 00:39:25,010
- The Jeju place might have one, I think.
- Right.

1059
00:39:25,010 --> 00:39:26,336
- I think so too.
- Yeah.

1060
00:39:26,336 --> 00:39:28,063
Let's ask them to get us a place with one.

1061
00:39:28,063 --> 00:39:30,583
[Their hearts are already by the Jeju seaside]

1062
00:39:30,583 --> 00:39:33,322
- Usually residence-style accommodations...
- Yeah.

1063
00:39:33,322 --> 00:39:35,775
have washing machines.

1064
00:39:35,775 --> 00:39:39,297
[Planning to solve lodging and laundry at once]

1065
00:39:39,297 --> 00:39:40,787
[Momentary focus]
Wait a second.

1066
00:39:40,787 --> 00:39:44,197
- Say we get to Gwangju International Airport.
- Yeah.

1067
00:39:44,197 --> 00:39:46,018
- And there are no plane tickets at all.
- Yeah.

1068
00:39:46,018 --> 00:39:48,093
[Q: Stay in Gwangju if no plane tickets?]
Then we'll just stay in Gwangju...

1069
00:39:48,093 --> 00:39:49,921
[Okay, discussion over]

1070
00:39:49,921 --> 00:39:52,097
Then we'll just go to Mudeungsan Mountain.

1071
00:39:52,097 --> 00:39:54,592
And the Songjeong-ri bakery.

1072
00:39:54,592 --> 00:39:56,092
- Say there are plane tickets.
- Yeah.

1073
00:39:56,092 --> 00:39:57,986
[Q: What if the flight is in a few hours?]
But we'd have to wait like

1074
00:39:57,986 --> 00:39:59,911
- four, five, six hours.
- Yeah.

1075
00:39:59,911 --> 00:40:01,527
Still Jeju then?

1076
00:40:01,527 --> 00:40:03,134
Then we can look around Gwangju first...

1077
00:40:03,134 --> 00:40:04,593
- And then go to Jeju?
- Yeah.

1078
00:40:04,593 --> 00:40:06,191
[Okay, discussion over]
Okay.

1079
00:40:06,191 --> 00:40:07,762
If there are tickets,
then it's definitely Jeju.

1080
00:40:07,762 --> 00:40:09,012
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

1081
00:40:09,759 --> 00:40:10,753
What about you, Yumi?

1082
00:40:10,753 --> 00:40:12,517
- Yeah, sounds good.
- Okay.

1083
00:40:12,517 --> 00:40:15,040
[The trio really clicks well together]

1084
00:40:15,040 --> 00:40:17,477
There's no need to talk about it any further.

1085
00:40:18,208 --> 00:40:22,272
[After making plans, the sleepiness kicks in]

1086
00:40:22,272 --> 00:40:24,567
[While the trio sleeps soundly]

1087
00:40:24,567 --> 00:40:27,326
[Our driver passes through a tunnel]

1088
00:40:29,299 --> 00:40:31,298
[Toward Gwangju and Hwasun]

1089
00:40:31,298 --> 00:40:34,705
[Speeding smoothly along the highway]

1090
00:40:34,705 --> 00:40:36,966
[At the Gwangju-Hwasun junction]

1091
00:40:36,966 --> 00:40:39,129
[Heads into Gwangju]

1092
00:40:39,129 --> 00:40:40,980
[Yawn]

1093
00:40:41,733 --> 00:40:43,508
Wow, I slept well.

1094
00:40:43,508 --> 00:40:46,536
[As they slept, the bus entered downtown]
Feels like we've really entered the city now.

1095
00:40:47,132 --> 00:40:48,662
Oh my, it's the city.

1096
00:40:48,662 --> 00:40:51,893
[The city arrived while the trio was asleep]
It's the city. We're back in the city.

1097
00:40:51,893 --> 00:40:53,795
[The moment they step onto the ground]

1098
00:40:53,795 --> 00:40:55,885
- Information desk!
- To the information desk.

1099
00:40:55,885 --> 00:40:58,275
[Finding the information desk
has become routine now]

1100
00:40:58,275 --> 00:41:00,811
We're trying to get to the airport,
how do we get there?

1101
00:41:00,811 --> 00:41:03,451
- Which airport?
- Gwangju Airport.

1102
00:41:03,451 --> 00:41:07,479
Use the underpass here and
take Bus No. 2 from the other side.

1103
00:41:07,479 --> 00:41:08,972
[Politely thanking them]
Ah, yes, thank you.

1104
00:41:08,972 --> 00:41:10,320
Go through the underpass and...

1105
00:41:10,320 --> 00:41:11,625
- take Bus No. 2 on the other side.
- Bus No. 2!

1106
00:41:11,625 --> 00:41:12,766
- The other side?
- Yeah.

1107
00:41:12,766 --> 00:41:14,799
[Parrot strategy so they won't forget]

1108
00:41:14,799 --> 00:41:16,808
Here, here.

1109
00:41:16,808 --> 00:41:19,696
[Exit 2, city bus &amp; taxi stop]
We need to go to the city bus stop.

1110
00:41:21,315 --> 00:41:25,009
[Following guide Woo Shik outside]
We need to take the city bus here. Over there.

1111
00:41:25,009 --> 00:41:27,636
We really came to the city.

1112
00:41:27,636 --> 00:41:30,469
[Wandering around, soaking in the city vibes]
The air feels different too.

1113
00:41:31,350 --> 00:41:34,253
[Found the underpass]
Go this way, and cross over.

1114
00:41:34,253 --> 00:41:37,522
[1. Go through the underpass]
Cross over and take Bus No. 2.

1115
00:41:37,522 --> 00:41:39,087
"We love Gwangju!"

1116
00:41:39,087 --> 00:41:40,908
"We love," "I love" these things are...

1117
00:41:40,908 --> 00:41:42,312
everywhere no matter where you go.

1118
00:41:42,312 --> 00:41:44,173
Right.

1119
00:41:44,173 --> 00:41:45,222
[Before long, they're going upstairs]

1120
00:41:45,222 --> 00:41:47,064
- Ugh.
- It's cold.

1121
00:41:47,064 --> 00:41:50,201
[A whole lot of them]

1122
00:41:50,201 --> 00:41:52,048
[Arrived on the other side]

1123
00:41:52,048 --> 00:41:54,178
- Here?
- Yeah.

1124
00:41:54,178 --> 00:41:56,179
[2. On the other side]
- Bus No. 2 from here. - I think over there!

1125
00:41:56,858 --> 00:41:58,125
Let's go over there.

1126
00:41:58,125 --> 00:42:00,519
[All that's left is boarding Bus 02]

1127
00:42:00,519 --> 00:42:02,986
It's only a few stops away.

1128
00:42:02,986 --> 00:42:04,713
It comes in nine minutes.

1129
00:42:04,713 --> 00:42:07,112
[Seat Bus 02, 9 min]
- It's here, right? - Yeah.

1130
00:42:07,112 --> 00:42:09,279
This is going smoothly.

1131
00:42:09,279 --> 00:42:10,694
[As they happily wait for the bus]

1132
00:42:10,694 --> 00:42:11,750
Nice!

1133
00:42:11,750 --> 00:42:14,032
- Ah, this...
- Jeju will be warm, right?

1134
00:42:14,032 --> 00:42:16,895
Oh, should we check the weather in Jeju?

1135
00:42:16,895 --> 00:42:19,892
- Right, we don't have phones.
- Oh right, we don't have phones.

1136
00:42:21,114 --> 00:42:24,326
But Jeju weather changes a lot...
raining and stopping and all that.

1137
00:42:24,326 --> 00:42:25,414
Because it's an island.

1138
00:42:25,414 --> 00:42:29,274
Wow, this is gonna get interesting.

1139
00:42:30,047 --> 00:42:31,188
I think once we get the tickets,

1140
00:42:31,188 --> 00:42:33,273
- we'll finally relax a little.
- Right.

1141
00:42:33,273 --> 00:42:35,006
Oh, should we eat the Dubai Chewy Cookie now?

1142
00:42:35,006 --> 00:42:36,642
- We're bored.
- I don't want any right now.

1143
00:42:36,642 --> 00:42:38,773
- I want some.
- Me too.

1144
00:42:38,773 --> 00:42:40,966
[Rummaging around]

1145
00:42:40,966 --> 00:42:42,499
[Precious]

1146
00:42:42,499 --> 00:42:43,575
How much can I eat?

1147
00:42:43,575 --> 00:42:45,049
- Eat half, half.
- Half.

1148
00:42:45,049 --> 00:42:46,423
- Can I eat up to here?
- Yeah.

1149
00:42:46,423 --> 00:42:48,515
It got chewy.

1150
00:42:49,303 --> 00:42:52,096
[Chewy]

1151
00:42:52,096 --> 00:42:54,074
[Taking it over]

1152
00:42:54,074 --> 00:42:57,368
[Dubai Chewy Cookie, come right into my mouth]

1153
00:43:01,279 --> 00:43:02,276
It's good though?

1154
00:43:02,276 --> 00:43:03,789
- It's good, right? Try it.
- Is it good?

1155
00:43:03,789 --> 00:43:04,817
It's too...

1156
00:43:04,817 --> 00:43:06,092
[Yumi takes over next]

1157
00:43:06,092 --> 00:43:07,959
[Big bite in one go]
Hey!

1158
00:43:07,959 --> 00:43:10,768
I thought you said you'd only eat a little?

1159
00:43:10,768 --> 00:43:12,264
Jeez.

1160
00:43:12,264 --> 00:43:14,546
Wait, didn't he give it to me to finish it all?

1161
00:43:14,546 --> 00:43:17,999
[The trio is great at sharing food]

1162
00:43:17,999 --> 00:43:21,138
Wait, let's drink some water first.

1163
00:43:21,138 --> 00:43:24,692
[With the plain bottled water
they stocked up on in Namwon]

1164
00:43:24,692 --> 00:43:28,235
[They wet their throats]

1165
00:43:29,052 --> 00:43:33,025
[Meanwhile, a bus approaches from afar]

1166
00:43:33,025 --> 00:43:34,407
- Huh? Hey, number 2.
- Oh, right!

1167
00:43:34,407 --> 00:43:37,075
[The bus comes by faster than expected]

1168
00:43:37,075 --> 00:43:40,836
[They hurriedly run over]

1169
00:43:42,300 --> 00:43:43,596
[Safe for now]

1170
00:43:43,596 --> 00:43:46,831
- Seo Jun, the regular fare is 1,800 won.
- Yeah.

1171
00:43:46,831 --> 00:43:48,581
- Tell them there are three people.
- Take out 6,000 won, yeah.

1172
00:43:48,581 --> 00:43:50,789
- Wait, wait here.
- Yeah, let them go first.

1173
00:43:50,789 --> 00:43:52,645
[Planning to pay 6,000 won in cash]

1174
00:43:52,645 --> 00:43:55,562
- Sir, this goes to the airport, right?
- Yeah.

1175
00:43:56,333 --> 00:43:57,561
[Now all they have to do is get on]

1176
00:43:57,561 --> 00:44:00,045
There are three of us, can we pay cash?

1177
00:44:00,985 --> 00:44:02,340
- Cash isn't accepted.
- He said cash doesn't work.

1178
00:44:02,340 --> 00:44:03,386
You have to do a bank transfer.

1179
00:44:03,386 --> 00:44:04,411
- A bank transfer?
- Yeah.

1180
00:44:04,411 --> 00:44:06,075
- I'll pay for it first and later...
- I'll transfer the money for you.

1181
00:44:06,075 --> 00:44:07,434
- 1,800 won.
- Yes.

1182
00:44:07,434 --> 00:44:09,313
- Three people.
- Three people.

1183
00:44:09,313 --> 00:44:11,223
- Just get on first.
- You'll need to write it down.

1184
00:44:11,223 --> 00:44:12,229
- Okay.
- Okay, thank you.

1185
00:44:12,229 --> 00:44:14,847
[They barely board thanks to the crew]

1186
00:44:14,847 --> 00:44:15,893
Three people...

1187
00:44:15,893 --> 00:44:17,900
[Getting to Jeju isn't easy]

1188
00:44:17,900 --> 00:44:21,493
- Oh, that surprised me.
- On the credit transfer request form...

1189
00:44:21,493 --> 00:44:23,453
Confirmed. Agree...

1190
00:44:24,235 --> 00:44:26,430
Because you don't have phones,
you can't do a bank transfer.

1191
00:44:26,430 --> 00:44:27,617
That's true.

1192
00:44:27,617 --> 00:44:28,658
[Really feeling the absence now]

1193
00:44:28,658 --> 00:44:29,795
- I'll do it for you,
- Okay.

1194
00:44:29,795 --> 00:44:31,516
- and then you can just give me the money.
- Yep.

1195
00:44:31,516 --> 00:44:33,465
- How much was it? Per person?
- 1,800 won.

1196
00:44:33,465 --> 00:44:35,667
Wow, that's not bad.

1197
00:44:35,667 --> 00:44:36,757
[Transferring money]

1198
00:44:36,757 --> 00:44:38,435
Did our staff get on too?

1199
00:44:38,435 --> 00:44:39,700
Yeah, they did.

1200
00:44:39,700 --> 00:44:41,218
[5,400 won transferred]

1201
00:44:41,218 --> 00:44:44,107
But since I paid with my own money,
could I get reimbursed right away?

1202
00:44:44,107 --> 00:44:45,975
Oh, okay.

1203
00:44:45,975 --> 00:44:47,059
Did you transfer it?

1204
00:44:47,059 --> 00:44:49,180
- Let me confirm first whether you did.
- Ah, okay.

1205
00:44:49,180 --> 00:44:50,932
[Maximum strictness]

1206
00:44:50,932 --> 00:44:52,033
Take a look at this.

1207
00:44:52,033 --> 00:44:55,037
5,400 won for Gwangju transportation.

1208
00:44:55,037 --> 00:44:56,775
- Okay.
- Yeah.

1209
00:44:57,712 --> 00:44:58,786
You have change, right?

1210
00:44:58,786 --> 00:45:00,664
- Ah, yes, I do.
- Yeah.

1211
00:45:02,411 --> 00:45:03,570
- Change first...
- Oh, okay.

1212
00:45:03,570 --> 00:45:05,583
How much should I give back?
I can't do the math.

1213
00:45:05,583 --> 00:45:07,699
It's 4,600 won.

1214
00:45:07,699 --> 00:45:09,502
You can give another 1,000 won too.

1215
00:45:09,502 --> 00:45:11,418
- Ah, 5,600 won then.
- Just give 5,000 won.

1216
00:45:11,418 --> 00:45:12,618
Just give 5,000 won.

1217
00:45:12,618 --> 00:45:13,668
[Nope]

1218
00:45:13,668 --> 00:45:15,774
[-5,400 won. Remaining: 233,610 won]

1219
00:45:15,774 --> 00:45:17,402
[Settlement complete]
- Thank you. - Thank you.

1220
00:45:17,402 --> 00:45:18,804
Thank you!

1221
00:45:18,804 --> 00:45:21,556
We're barely stepping on Gwangju soil
before going to Jeju.

1222
00:45:21,556 --> 00:45:24,483
- We just glanced at "I Love Gwangju."
- "We love Gwangju."

1223
00:45:24,483 --> 00:45:26,823
But it's not over until it's over.

1224
00:45:26,823 --> 00:45:28,726
- Right.
- We haven't gone all the way yet.

1225
00:45:28,726 --> 00:45:30,769
Come on, what are you talking about?

1226
00:45:30,769 --> 00:45:33,582
Even just pork noodles sound delicious.

1227
00:45:33,582 --> 00:45:35,522
[Actually, Po-po is excited about Jeju too]
- Dombae. - Oh, dombae pork.

1228
00:45:35,522 --> 00:45:38,008
- But Jeju is really expensive, right?
- Yeah.

1229
00:45:38,008 --> 00:45:39,939
- It is expensive.
- Let's go to the market, if we...

1230
00:45:39,939 --> 00:45:41,992
[Nods]
Let's go to the market! I like markets.

1231
00:45:41,992 --> 00:45:45,415
Come to think of it,
we haven't gone to a market yet.

1232
00:45:46,165 --> 00:45:48,540
So are we drinking Halla*** soju today?

1233
00:45:49,664 --> 00:45:52,794
- That sounds amazing.
- We really drink all kinds of soju.

1234
00:45:52,794 --> 00:45:54,645
[They are still in Gwangju]
Amazing.

1235
00:45:54,645 --> 00:45:56,218
That Halla*** clear bottle.

1236
00:45:56,218 --> 00:45:57,326
Yeah.

1237
00:45:57,326 --> 00:45:59,965
[I'm so excited for Jeju]

1238
00:45:59,965 --> 00:46:01,872
What time do you think it is now?

1239
00:46:02,567 --> 00:46:04,547
It's 14:24!

1240
00:46:05,614 --> 00:46:07,794
- Where?
- It's over there at the very front.

1241
00:46:07,794 --> 00:46:11,527
[Even a clock is fun when I think of Jeju]
- Where? - At the very top in front.

1242
00:46:11,527 --> 00:46:13,255
[The sunglasses trio squints together]

1243
00:46:13,255 --> 00:46:15,041
25 minutes, 14:25.

1244
00:46:15,041 --> 00:46:16,169
Ah, on the front of that bus?

1245
00:46:16,169 --> 00:46:18,075
- Oh, there it is!
- It's 14:25.

1246
00:46:18,075 --> 00:46:20,392
- The timing's good.
- Yeah.

1247
00:46:20,392 --> 00:46:24,122
It'll probably be evening when we get to Jeju.

1248
00:46:24,122 --> 00:46:27,279
Don't say it in advance yet.
Talk after we buy the tickets.

1249
00:46:27,279 --> 00:46:28,712
[But you've been talking about it
this whole time...]

1250
00:46:28,712 --> 00:46:30,749
Because I'm nervous. The plane...

1251
00:46:30,749 --> 00:46:33,917
[Will the trio be able to leave safely?]

1252
00:46:33,917 --> 00:46:37,163
[This stop is Airport Station]

1253
00:46:38,001 --> 00:46:40,767
But I don't see the airport?

1254
00:46:40,767 --> 00:46:44,933
[They're clearly almost there,
but there are barely any buildings...]

1255
00:46:49,721 --> 00:46:51,814
Wait, where are the airplanes?

1256
00:46:52,797 --> 00:46:55,304
[Looking around]

1257
00:46:55,304 --> 00:46:58,543
- The airplanes...
- I don't see any.

1258
00:46:58,543 --> 00:47:00,388
It kind of feels like
there aren't any planes though.

1259
00:47:00,388 --> 00:47:02,993
- There are no planes.
- There aren't any.

1260
00:47:02,993 --> 00:47:04,834
[Hahahahaha]
Don't do that.

1261
00:47:04,834 --> 00:47:07,699
Huh? Wait... isn't it the next stop?

1262
00:47:07,699 --> 00:47:10,695
Where's the airport?
Why isn't there an airport?

1263
00:47:10,695 --> 00:47:12,441
- We need to get off.
- Let's just get off first.

1264
00:47:12,441 --> 00:47:15,072
[They get off at Airport Station as planned]
It is Airport Station though.

1265
00:47:18,001 --> 00:47:20,764
- Is this right?
- Let's cross over!

1266
00:47:20,764 --> 00:47:23,317
[The trio's current location is]
The subway's over there.

1267
00:47:23,317 --> 00:47:27,686
[from Gwangju Airport
about a 12-minute walk away]

1268
00:47:27,686 --> 00:47:30,389
[They have to pass through the subway station]

1269
00:47:30,389 --> 00:47:32,560
I still don't see any planes, but let's go.

1270
00:47:32,560 --> 00:47:34,335
I don't see any planes though.

1271
00:47:34,335 --> 00:47:36,215
Where does it say Gwangju Airport?

1272
00:47:36,215 --> 00:47:37,756
Cross over...

1273
00:47:37,756 --> 00:47:40,570
[Luckily, they seem to be on the right track]
- Oh, over there? - Cross over... yeah.

1274
00:47:40,570 --> 00:47:42,104
Wouldn't we just go down here?

1275
00:47:42,104 --> 00:47:43,110
Feels like if we go down there,

1276
00:47:43,110 --> 00:47:45,012
- everything will work out, right?
- Feels like it'll connect through, right?

1277
00:47:45,012 --> 00:47:48,405
[Okay then, let's head down]

1278
00:47:49,212 --> 00:47:50,738
[Then they hear the sound
of a plane taking off]

1279
00:47:50,738 --> 00:47:52,054
Huh? That's the sound of a plane.

1280
00:47:52,054 --> 00:47:53,381
- Oh.
- Yeah, I hear a sound.

1281
00:47:53,381 --> 00:47:55,606
[Immediately relieved by the airplane sound]

1282
00:47:55,606 --> 00:47:59,552
[Their steps become lighter
after hearing the airplane]

1283
00:48:00,589 --> 00:48:02,630
Exit 2!

1284
00:48:02,630 --> 00:48:03,835
[Hitting the door]

1285
00:48:05,822 --> 00:48:07,002
[As expected, a man with charm
but no sense of direction...]

1286
00:48:07,002 --> 00:48:09,402
Seriously.

1287
00:48:09,402 --> 00:48:12,077
Choi Woo Shik, seriously...

1288
00:48:12,077 --> 00:48:13,658
Why is the sky so dull today,

1289
00:48:13,658 --> 00:48:15,544
and why is there seriously nothing around here?

1290
00:48:15,544 --> 00:48:18,350
[Their emotional rollercoaster never stops...]
But seriously, why is there nothing here?

1291
00:48:18,350 --> 00:48:21,545
[Well, that makes sense because...]

1292
00:48:21,545 --> 00:48:23,912
[All they can see from Airport Station is...]

1293
00:48:23,912 --> 00:48:27,399
[Endless roads and cars...]

1294
00:48:28,000 --> 00:48:29,634
- I think it's over there?
- Yeah.

1295
00:48:29,634 --> 00:48:31,043
- It's over there.
- Let's go.

1296
00:48:31,043 --> 00:48:32,636
[Arrived at the airport]

1297
00:48:32,636 --> 00:48:34,492
Seo Jun, where are you?

1298
00:48:34,492 --> 00:48:35,779
[With Seo Jun]

1299
00:48:35,779 --> 00:48:37,025
I'm here.

1300
00:48:37,025 --> 00:48:38,505
[With Yumi]

1301
00:48:38,505 --> 00:48:40,270
It's so funny that
we actually came to the airport.

1302
00:48:40,270 --> 00:48:41,900
[Right...]

1303
00:48:41,900 --> 00:48:44,086
- Wow.
- Hopefully there are tickets.

1304
00:48:44,086 --> 00:48:45,947
Why do I keep imagining us getting back

1305
00:48:45,947 --> 00:48:50,261
- on that bus and going somewhere else?
- What are you talking about? No way.

1306
00:48:50,261 --> 00:48:52,918
- I feel like we're heading back on that bus.
- That would be such a shame, but...

1307
00:48:52,918 --> 00:48:54,155
that won't happen.

1308
00:48:54,155 --> 00:48:56,892
- Oh! It's T'***!
- Oh, there's T'***.

1309
00:48:56,892 --> 00:48:59,153
- Oh, it's going in right now?
- Hurry, try running!

1310
00:48:59,153 --> 00:49:00,979
Ah, there'll be another one.

1311
00:49:00,979 --> 00:49:04,302
We're treating airplanes like buses right now.

1312
00:49:04,302 --> 00:49:06,425
Ah, I'm excited. This is gonna be so fun.

1313
00:49:06,425 --> 00:49:07,904
I really wish there was one.

1314
00:49:07,904 --> 00:49:10,025
- It'd be so funny if there actually were.
- I really hope there are seats.

1315
00:49:10,025 --> 00:49:11,486
[The trio's desperate wish to go to Jeju...]

1316
00:49:11,486 --> 00:49:15,172
[Will their wish come true?]

1317
00:49:16,746 --> 00:49:18,465
Hey, the schedule!

1318
00:49:18,465 --> 00:49:20,412
There is, there is!

1319
00:49:20,412 --> 00:49:22,725
Then what time is it now? Three o'clock...

1320
00:49:22,725 --> 00:49:24,052
Oh, that's arrivals though?

1321
00:49:24,052 --> 00:49:25,404
Let's just go first.

1322
00:49:25,404 --> 00:49:26,784
- Departures. Second floor.
- No, the plane tickets.

1323
00:49:26,784 --> 00:49:28,265
- Departures are on the second floor.
- The plane tickets.

1324
00:49:28,265 --> 00:49:29,833
[Oops, buying the plane tickets comes first...]
Tickets, tickets.

1325
00:49:29,833 --> 00:49:32,512
We don't have tickets yet. You know it, right?

1326
00:49:32,512 --> 00:49:34,512
[You need a ticket to board a plane]
Wait, wait.

1327
00:49:34,512 --> 00:49:38,329
J** Air. T'***.

1328
00:49:38,329 --> 00:49:40,190
- Asi***.
- This is the check-in though?

1329
00:49:40,190 --> 00:49:41,657
Where do you buy tickets on-site?

1330
00:49:41,657 --> 00:49:43,298
- Should we ask first?
- The ticket counter is over there.

1331
00:49:43,298 --> 00:49:46,131
[First, they found the ticket counter]
- Where? - Over there.

1332
00:49:46,131 --> 00:49:47,818
- Should we ask?
- Asi***?

1333
00:49:47,818 --> 00:49:49,299
- Yeah.
- I think it's gonna be expensive.

1334
00:49:49,299 --> 00:49:51,578
[On-site ticket challenge START]

1335
00:49:51,578 --> 00:49:54,419
Excuse me, can we buy tickets right now?

1336
00:49:54,419 --> 00:49:55,846
- You didn't make a reservation?
- No, we didn't.

1337
00:49:55,846 --> 00:49:57,373
Because we don't have our phones.

1338
00:49:57,373 --> 00:50:00,312
- But with our IDs, it should all work, right?
- Yes, we can look it up.

1339
00:50:00,312 --> 00:50:02,712
[You can book with just an ID]
- Let's go. - Let's try.

1340
00:50:02,712 --> 00:50:05,606
[Will there actually be
tickets available on-site?]

1341
00:50:05,606 --> 00:50:09,201
We didn't make reservations,
so we need to buy tickets here.

1342
00:50:09,201 --> 00:50:10,208
Where are you going?

1343
00:50:10,208 --> 00:50:11,508
- We're trying to go to Jeju Island.
- Jeju Island.

1344
00:50:11,508 --> 00:50:14,002
There are no seats available today.

1345
00:50:14,002 --> 00:50:15,441
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

1346
00:50:15,441 --> 00:50:17,241
Would you like to wait on standby?

1347
00:50:17,241 --> 00:50:19,007
If cancellation tickets come up,
you'll be able to go.

1348
00:50:19,007 --> 00:50:21,719
[Cancellation tickets?]

1349
00:50:21,719 --> 00:50:24,085
- For standby, the 15:40 flight...
- 15:40?

1350
00:50:24,085 --> 00:50:25,903
First, you need to write down your names.

1351
00:50:25,903 --> 00:50:28,277
- Should we just put our names down first?
- Over here...

1352
00:50:28,277 --> 00:50:29,957
There are already people waiting.

1353
00:50:29,957 --> 00:50:31,791
- Oh, yeah?
- Since this started in the morning,

1354
00:50:31,791 --> 00:50:33,498
there's a chance there won't be any seats left.

1355
00:50:33,498 --> 00:50:35,072
Everyone boarding should
write down their names.

1356
00:50:35,072 --> 00:50:36,101
Just this much.

1357
00:50:36,101 --> 00:50:38,800
[For now, only the minimum number of
passengers is recorded (3 cast, 3 staff)]

1358
00:50:38,800 --> 00:50:41,288
[30 minutes left until the deadline]
If you come at this time, you can check then.

1359
00:50:41,288 --> 00:50:43,673
- If cancellation tickets open up by then.
- Aha.

1360
00:50:43,673 --> 00:50:45,717
Got it.

1361
00:50:45,717 --> 00:50:49,403
[If more than 3 tickets are canceled
within 30 minutes, they can go]

1362
00:50:49,403 --> 00:50:51,518
- You knew that already, honestly, right?
- Liar.

1363
00:50:51,518 --> 00:50:52,572
Honestly, you knew, right?

1364
00:50:52,572 --> 00:50:53,578
[Taking their frustration out
on the staff for no reason]

1365
00:50:53,578 --> 00:50:55,691
- Honestly, you knew!
- You knew!

1366
00:50:55,691 --> 00:50:59,382
But actually, we really
wanted to enjoy Gwangju anyway.

1367
00:50:59,382 --> 00:51:02,104
- We just came to check out Gwangju Airport.
- We just came to look around the airport.

1368
00:51:02,104 --> 00:51:04,223
- Just wondering what the airport looks like?
- Yeah.

1369
00:51:04,223 --> 00:51:06,787
- It's just our routine.
- Oh, I see.

1370
00:51:06,787 --> 00:51:09,408
But if we wait, do you think
seats will open up?

1371
00:51:09,408 --> 00:51:10,823
- I think they might.
- I don't think they will.

1372
00:51:10,823 --> 00:51:12,116
- I don't think five seats will open up.
- What time does your flight leave?

1373
00:51:12,116 --> 00:51:14,271
- It's the 15:40 flight.
- 15:40.

1374
00:51:14,271 --> 00:51:15,838
- 15:40?
- Yeah.

1375
00:51:15,838 --> 00:51:18,542
- Should we at least grab a coffee?
- Yeah, let's go to that café.

1376
00:51:18,542 --> 00:51:19,578
Okay.

1377
00:51:19,578 --> 00:51:21,632
I was actually really excited just now.

1378
00:51:21,632 --> 00:51:23,771
Well, that's enough, I guess.

1379
00:51:27,876 --> 00:51:29,353
This is such a bummer though.

1380
00:51:29,353 --> 00:51:31,266
- I know.
- What should we do?

1381
00:51:31,266 --> 00:51:33,798
[Woo Shik still can't let it go]
But if we wait, won't seats open up?

1382
00:51:33,798 --> 00:51:35,818
[Seo Jun is half giving up]
I don't think they will.

1383
00:51:37,511 --> 00:51:39,857
[2:58 PM / Airport café]
Alright then,

1384
00:51:39,857 --> 00:51:41,578
the problem is...

1385
00:51:41,578 --> 00:51:43,538
where should we even start?

1386
00:51:43,538 --> 00:51:45,423
Ah, then, go to the accommodation first?

1387
00:51:45,423 --> 00:51:48,973
- Accommodation.
- Where do we book it? In Jeju or in Gwangju?

1388
00:51:48,973 --> 00:51:50,503
We should book it here.

1389
00:51:50,503 --> 00:51:53,270
Then should we book one
for you in Gwangju? What now?

1390
00:51:53,270 --> 00:51:55,125
Ah, but honestly, I still feel it's a waste.

1391
00:51:55,125 --> 00:51:56,457
I think seats will open up if we wait.

1392
00:51:56,457 --> 00:51:58,590
Then should we wait until 15:40?

1393
00:51:58,590 --> 00:52:00,691
- Ah, the flight is at 15:40, right?
- Yeah.

1394
00:52:00,691 --> 00:52:01,937
Then the seats would open up before that.

1395
00:52:01,937 --> 00:52:02,957
20 minutes.

1396
00:52:02,957 --> 00:52:05,315
Earlier they said we just have to
go down at 15:20.

1397
00:52:05,315 --> 00:52:07,546
- Ah, at 15:20?
- Yeah.

1398
00:52:07,546 --> 00:52:11,466
If one family cancels,
that's basically four seats right there.

1399
00:52:11,466 --> 00:52:12,956
[At least four seats could open up]
Right.

1400
00:52:12,956 --> 00:52:15,599
Then if three seats open up,
at least we'll get on.

1401
00:52:15,599 --> 00:52:18,023
We can bring this.
You guys just take the next flight.

1402
00:52:18,023 --> 00:52:20,391
[They seriously look ready to leave
with just the three of them...]

1403
00:52:20,391 --> 00:52:21,903
How do you feel?

1404
00:52:21,903 --> 00:52:23,950
Well...

1405
00:52:24,623 --> 00:52:26,004
I was so excited

1406
00:52:26,004 --> 00:52:31,529
thinking about eating cutlassfish
and black pork in Jeju.

1407
00:52:31,529 --> 00:52:32,738
It's good.

1408
00:52:32,738 --> 00:52:34,837
Thinking about going to Jeju
soon makes me so excited.

1409
00:52:34,837 --> 00:52:36,788
[Super positive]
Oh.

1410
00:52:36,788 --> 00:52:38,898
- You still haven't given up.
- Nope.

1411
00:52:38,898 --> 00:52:42,125
[Now that she said it out loud,
she feels awkward]

1412
00:52:44,722 --> 00:52:46,542
I'm giving up for now.

1413
00:52:47,414 --> 00:52:49,877
- But sometimes I...
- 15:40! 15:40!

1414
00:52:49,877 --> 00:52:53,022
Simultaneous check-in now open!

1415
00:52:53,022 --> 00:52:54,169
What did she just say?

1416
00:52:54,169 --> 00:52:56,088
- She said simultaneous check-in.
- Oh...

1417
00:52:56,088 --> 00:52:57,222
15:40...

1418
00:52:57,222 --> 00:52:58,744
[People with tickets are boarding...]

1419
00:52:58,744 --> 00:53:01,222
- Wow, they're all going.
- I'm jealous.

1420
00:53:01,222 --> 00:53:03,009
I'm jealous.

1421
00:53:03,009 --> 00:53:05,315
Even the dog over there gets to go.

1422
00:53:06,275 --> 00:53:08,762
These days, you absolutely
have to make reservations.

1423
00:53:08,762 --> 00:53:09,975
Well, that's true.

1424
00:53:09,975 --> 00:53:12,288
- And it's Friday too.
- Oh, right.

1425
00:53:12,288 --> 00:53:14,065
[It's even the start of a long holiday weekend]

1426
00:53:14,065 --> 00:53:15,947
What would you do if only two seats opened up?

1427
00:53:15,947 --> 00:53:17,824
- What if only two seats open up?
- We can't go.

1428
00:53:17,824 --> 00:53:19,424
Ah, okay.

1429
00:53:19,424 --> 00:53:21,520
- So we're not going, right?
- We have to go together no matter what.

1430
00:53:21,520 --> 00:53:24,733
Of course. You really are something, Yumi.

1431
00:53:26,095 --> 00:53:28,002
Wait, were you thinking something else?

1432
00:53:28,002 --> 00:53:30,815
We are one right now. We're all Ps, MBTI Ps.

1433
00:53:30,815 --> 00:53:32,597
A gathering of Ps.

1434
00:53:32,597 --> 00:53:34,275
We're all Ps.

1435
00:53:34,275 --> 00:53:36,755
But what if there's a flight tomorrow morning?

1436
00:53:36,755 --> 00:53:37,895
- Ah, tomorrow's tickets?
- Yeah.

1437
00:53:37,895 --> 00:53:39,941
We should think of different
possibilities in advance.

1438
00:53:39,941 --> 00:53:41,676
That's such a J thing.

1439
00:53:41,676 --> 00:53:43,444
Such a J. We're not compatible.

1440
00:53:43,444 --> 00:53:46,043
[The younger guys' teasing doesn't faze her]
Ah, we should go ask now.

1441
00:53:46,043 --> 00:53:47,582
It's almost time.

1442
00:53:47,582 --> 00:53:50,031
Yumi, stay here for a second
and watch the luggage.

1443
00:53:50,031 --> 00:53:51,269
- We'll go check.
- Yeah.

1444
00:53:51,269 --> 00:53:52,393
I'll watch the luggage.

1445
00:53:52,393 --> 00:53:54,028
Okay, luggage covered too.

1446
00:53:54,028 --> 00:53:56,701
- Then just bring your IDs.
- Yeah.

1447
00:53:56,701 --> 00:53:59,684
So if just one family cancels, we're good.

1448
00:53:59,684 --> 00:54:02,154
I hope everyone above us is one big family.

1449
00:54:02,154 --> 00:54:03,312
