01:03:11,224 --> 01:03:14,237
[There's also a computer
for the limited travelers]

1683
01:03:14,237 --> 01:03:16,630
- What market was it again?
- It doesn't come out here.

1684
01:03:16,630 --> 01:03:19,121
- Nongwon Market.
- Was it Yeongpung?

1685
01:03:19,121 --> 01:03:20,528
Then should we go eat Korean beef?

1686
01:03:20,528 --> 01:03:22,524
[Gwangju is also famous for raw Korean beef]

1687
01:03:22,524 --> 01:03:25,013
I'll search for "Gwangju Hanwoo ***."

1688
01:03:25,013 --> 01:03:26,334
Hanwoo ***.

1689
01:03:26,334 --> 01:03:27,964
Whoa.

1690
01:03:28,717 --> 01:03:30,437
This is exactly what I wanted to eat!

1691
01:03:30,437 --> 01:03:32,370
[Woo Shik especially loves raw beef]
- Mungtigi? - Yeah.

1692
01:03:32,370 --> 01:03:35,110
[About a 20-minute walk]
- Oh, Ssangchon? It's close. - Yeah.

1693
01:03:36,450 --> 01:03:39,427
But do we even have enough money for this?

1694
01:03:39,427 --> 01:03:41,310
About how much do you have left?

1695
01:03:41,310 --> 01:03:42,480
200,000 won.

1696
01:03:42,480 --> 01:03:44,374
- How much do we have left again?
- Oh, you still have 200,000 won?

1697
01:03:44,374 --> 01:03:47,511
[Can they actually afford it?]
But beef is gonna be expensive.

1698
01:03:47,511 --> 01:03:48,615
- Oh, it says it here.
- There it is, it's written there.

1699
01:03:48,615 --> 01:03:51,053
[About 70,000 won for 600g of raw beef]
- 70,000 won. - So it's 70,000 won.

1700
01:03:51,053 --> 01:03:52,336
70,000 won should be enough.

1701
01:03:52,336 --> 01:03:53,998
- Yeah.
- So that's actually for three servings?

1702
01:03:53,998 --> 01:03:56,169
- Yeah.
- Right, 600g is three servings.

1703
01:03:56,169 --> 01:03:58,844
But the price is fine,
so I think Hanwoo *** is a good option too.

1704
01:03:58,844 --> 01:04:01,424
[Dinner is Hanwoo *** for now]

1705
01:04:01,424 --> 01:04:03,801
Let's do this.

1706
01:04:03,801 --> 01:04:06,101
Let's go to the market in the morning
and have breakfast there.

1707
01:04:06,101 --> 01:04:07,232
Sounds good!

1708
01:04:07,232 --> 01:04:09,165
Gwangju, Jeju...

1709
01:04:09,165 --> 01:04:10,665
[They immediately start searching
for flights to Jeju...]

1710
01:04:10,665 --> 01:04:14,085
- Then, it'll come up.
- Uh, wait. Then it's way too expensive.

1711
01:04:14,085 --> 01:04:15,978
[Actually, Feb 28, the day they want to go...]
Let's first look it up.

1712
01:04:15,978 --> 01:04:17,762
[Feb 28 (Sat) Jeju trip, Mar 1 Independence
Movement Day, Mar 2 Substitute Holiday]

1713
01:04:17,762 --> 01:04:20,249
[It's a golden holiday weekend
with three days off]

1714
01:04:20,249 --> 01:04:24,119
[Flights to Jeju are either sold out
or extremely expensive]

1715
01:04:24,119 --> 01:04:25,798
[Will there even be tickets left for the 28th?]

1716
01:04:25,798 --> 01:04:27,946
- I don't think there are any left.
- Scroll down.

1717
01:04:27,946 --> 01:04:29,772
- There's one!
- There's one. J** Air.

1718
01:04:30,759 --> 01:04:33,699
[Lowest fare: 20:00 (Gwangju) to 20:55 (Jeju),
83,700 won per person]

1719
01:04:33,699 --> 01:04:35,597
Ah, the 8 PM one is the cheapest right now.

1720
01:04:35,597 --> 01:04:36,932
83,700 won.

1721
01:04:36,932 --> 01:04:40,269
- So for three people, that's 250,000 won?
- Right.

1722
01:04:40,269 --> 01:04:42,008
But that's too expensive.

1723
01:04:42,008 --> 01:04:43,549
Then we'd have to

1724
01:04:43,549 --> 01:04:44,973
- survive there with 4,900 won...
- It's this expensive?

1725
01:04:44,973 --> 01:04:46,337
[They'd have to eat and sleep on
about 49,000 won tomorrow]

1726
01:04:46,337 --> 01:04:48,047
49,000 won...

1727
01:04:48,047 --> 01:04:50,175
But wait. Time out!

1728
01:04:50,175 --> 01:04:51,613
Do we only have 30,000 won left now?

1729
01:04:51,613 --> 01:04:54,845
Yeah. And we'd need to get lodging with that.

1730
01:04:54,845 --> 01:04:57,438
But we might win lodging again.

1731
01:04:57,438 --> 01:04:59,058
Or you might win a car.

1732
01:04:59,058 --> 01:05:00,756
But that's all hypothetical, right?

1733
01:05:00,756 --> 01:05:03,697
If we draw the phone, we're basically screwed.

1734
01:05:03,697 --> 01:05:05,518
But that would be fun.

1735
01:05:05,518 --> 01:05:06,582
[Dopamine addict]

1736
01:05:06,582 --> 01:05:08,511
- Sleep at the airport?
- Just...

1737
01:05:08,511 --> 01:05:09,732
- there...
- I can sleep there.

1738
01:05:09,732 --> 01:05:12,701
We just need 30,000 won for dinner.

1739
01:05:12,701 --> 01:05:15,203
And then we travel around Jeju the next day.

1740
01:05:15,203 --> 01:05:17,143
We get money the next day, 300,000 won.

1741
01:05:17,143 --> 01:05:18,885
But if we want to book it,
we'd have to do it now.

1742
01:05:18,885 --> 01:05:21,364
We might not get tickets by tomorrow.

1743
01:05:21,364 --> 01:05:23,829
Think about it. If we really follow this rule,

1744
01:05:23,829 --> 01:05:26,190
we have to book it right now
with the money we currently have.

1745
01:05:26,190 --> 01:05:27,968
But we don't even have enough money right now.

1746
01:05:27,968 --> 01:05:29,123
[Current balance 229,910 won]
Well, you're right.

1747
01:05:29,123 --> 01:05:31,088
And since it's the weekend, prices are...

1748
01:05:31,088 --> 01:05:32,964
- Right.
- But what if...

1749
01:05:32,964 --> 01:05:35,090
we check tomorrow and there are still tickets?

1750
01:05:35,090 --> 01:05:37,128
- At the same price, 250,000 won.
- Yeah.

1751
01:05:37,128 --> 01:05:40,996
Then we'd just need to cover breakfast,
lunch, and dinner with 50,000 won.

1752
01:05:40,996 --> 01:05:42,527
Then what about lodging?

1753
01:05:42,527 --> 01:05:43,727
Because we're gonna win lodging.

1754
01:05:43,727 --> 01:05:46,020
[The same routine again]

1755
01:05:46,020 --> 01:05:48,753
Woo Shik, but by that logic, think about it.

1756
01:05:48,753 --> 01:05:50,339
We're going to the market
tomorrow morning, right?

1757
01:05:50,339 --> 01:05:52,837
Yeah, then we can't go to the market.
Because we have to go to Jeju.

1758
01:05:52,837 --> 01:05:55,085
- We'll just starve.
- Starve ourselves...

1759
01:05:55,085 --> 01:05:58,714
But the market might sell
buckwheat noodles really cheaply.

1760
01:05:58,714 --> 01:06:02,050
Or let's go to Ssangchon Station right now
and do a talent show.

1761
01:06:02,050 --> 01:06:04,837
- Put a hat down like this.
- Yeah, "Food donations only." Like that.

1762
01:06:04,837 --> 01:06:06,255
I mean, think about it.

1763
01:06:06,255 --> 01:06:08,111
- There are cheap foods at the market.
- Like noodles?

1764
01:06:08,111 --> 01:06:10,959
Or we can order one serving
of tteokbokki and share it.

1765
01:06:10,959 --> 01:06:15,330
But realistically,
Jeju seems kind of difficult.

1766
01:06:15,330 --> 01:06:17,757
["Let's go to Jeju", "We can't go to Jeju,"
100-minute Jeju debate]

1767
01:06:17,757 --> 01:06:19,283
This really doesn't make sense.

1768
01:06:19,283 --> 01:06:22,097
Then we should probably skip
Hanwoo *** today too.

1769
01:06:22,097 --> 01:06:24,770
But didn't we come here
to eat something delicious today?

1770
01:06:24,770 --> 01:06:26,404
["Let's just eat", hungry Jung Yumi]

1771
01:06:26,404 --> 01:06:28,289
There's a lot of delicious food in Jeju too.

1772
01:06:28,289 --> 01:06:31,413
No, we don't have money,
even if Jeju has good food.

1773
01:06:31,413 --> 01:06:32,427
- If we go to Jeju...
- Exactly.

1774
01:06:32,427 --> 01:06:34,170
That's why we're not eating Hanwoo *** today.

1775
01:06:34,170 --> 01:06:36,018
- But we came all the way to Gwangju?
- Then it's possible.

1776
01:06:36,018 --> 01:06:38,470
Yeah. We just don't eat Hanwoo *** today.

1777
01:06:39,150 --> 01:06:41,797
Then we basically came to Gwangju
just to sleep here?

1778
01:06:43,412 --> 01:06:44,903
Pretty much...

1779
01:06:44,903 --> 01:06:47,528
- Then we...
- For Jeju...

1780
01:06:47,528 --> 01:06:49,829
- it's kind of a stepping stone.
- Stepping stone...

1781
01:06:49,829 --> 01:06:52,881
[Still completely obsessed with Jeju]

1782
01:06:52,881 --> 01:06:54,574
Or we could just go there
and eat rice cake soup.

1783
01:06:54,574 --> 01:06:56,440
[The realist Seo Jun is slowly being persuaded]
Yeah. Because...

1784
01:06:56,440 --> 01:06:58,813
"Can we just order the dessert
rice cake soup?" Like that...

1785
01:06:58,813 --> 01:07:00,909
[Realizing how ridiculous what he just said is]

1786
01:07:00,909 --> 01:07:03,453
Or we go there, order only rice cake soup,

1787
01:07:03,453 --> 01:07:05,850
and keep looking at the next table
saying, "Ah, that looks good."

1788
01:07:05,850 --> 01:07:08,650
[The "make them pity us" strategy]
- "Ah, that looks good." - "Is it good?"

1789
01:07:10,923 --> 01:07:12,295
Can I just look it up once?

1790
01:07:12,295 --> 01:07:14,750
[Hungry Yumi finally steps in.]

1791
01:07:14,750 --> 01:07:16,638
[Looking for cheaper flights]
Keep discussing it quickly.

1792
01:07:16,638 --> 01:07:18,760
- What?
- You two keep discussing it.

1793
01:07:18,760 --> 01:07:21,440
[Debaters have lost all passion]
- We're done already. - We're done talking.

1794
01:07:21,440 --> 01:07:24,600
Now we just have to decide.
Hanwoo *** or Jeju Island?

1795
01:07:24,600 --> 01:07:28,170
[But big sis refuses to give up]
Ah, I do want to go to Hanwoo *** too.

1796
01:07:28,170 --> 01:07:30,689
[Attempt 1. Searching on Ko**** Air's official website]
- Did you log in, Yumi? - No, I just...

1797
01:07:30,689 --> 01:07:32,608
[No tickets for the 28th]
- There's nothing. - It says there aren't any.

1798
01:07:32,608 --> 01:07:34,549
[Attempt 2, Searching on
Asi***'s official website]

1799
01:07:34,549 --> 01:07:36,499
[Can't even search for it]
- What? - It's basically telling us not to go.

1800
01:07:36,499 --> 01:07:39,679
J**... then I'll check Je** Air as a last try.

1801
01:07:39,679 --> 01:07:40,839
Yeah...

1802
01:07:40,839 --> 01:07:42,965
[Attempt 3, Searching on
Je** Air's official website]

1803
01:07:42,965 --> 01:07:46,054
[No tickets at all for the 28th]
- Ah, nothing. - It's sold out.

1804
01:07:46,054 --> 01:07:49,269
See? Normally, it's like 23,000 won.

1805
01:07:49,269 --> 01:07:50,575
- If we had gone yesterday,
- Yeah.

1806
01:07:50,575 --> 01:07:54,003
- it would've been like 17,000 to 20,000 won.
- Seriously, if we'd gone yesterday...

1807
01:07:54,917 --> 01:07:56,089
What a shame.

1808
01:07:56,089 --> 01:07:58,295
Or...

1809
01:07:58,295 --> 01:07:59,924
how about this?

1810
01:07:59,924 --> 01:08:02,752
- Let's go to Jeju on the morning of March 1.
- Yeah.

1811
01:08:02,752 --> 01:08:04,372
[2/27 Today, 2/28 Jeju 3/1 Return to Seoul]
Yeah, sounds good.

1812
01:08:04,372 --> 01:08:06,238
- As a day trip.
- Sounds good.

1813
01:08:06,238 --> 01:08:08,578
- We come back in the evening.
- Sounds good.

1814
01:08:08,578 --> 01:08:10,467
[Plan B that breaks conventional thinking]

1815
01:08:10,467 --> 01:08:11,794
[Even the dreamer agrees]
- That's not bad. - Thanks.

1816
01:08:11,794 --> 01:08:13,561
Should I search it with three of us?

1817
01:08:13,561 --> 01:08:15,014
Yeah, March 1 morning.

1818
01:08:15,014 --> 01:08:17,298
[Will there be tickets
for the morning of 3/1 (Sun)?]

1819
01:08:17,298 --> 01:08:19,445
9 AM! Oh, there is one.

1820
01:08:19,445 --> 01:08:21,849
[Lowest fare, 48,810 won per person]

1821
01:08:21,849 --> 01:08:25,039
[48,810 won per person, 146,430 won for 3]
- 48,000 won. Not bad. - Nice.

1822
01:08:25,039 --> 01:08:26,395
- We're taking the 9 AM flight.
- Yeah.

1823
01:08:26,395 --> 01:08:28,218
We'll go eat some cutlassfish
or something and come back.

1824
01:08:28,218 --> 01:08:30,034
[The proposal is becoming very tempting]
Oh, nice!

1825
01:08:30,034 --> 01:08:32,914
So we do a day trip
and come back in the evening.

1826
01:08:32,914 --> 01:08:34,202
- Oh, nice.
- Nice!

1827
01:08:34,202 --> 01:08:35,368
- And do a livestream.
- Yeah.

1828
01:08:35,368 --> 01:08:36,616
- Right, on March 1st...
- Yeah.

1829
01:08:36,616 --> 01:08:38,783
We'll say, "Guess where we just came from,"

1830
01:08:38,783 --> 01:08:40,576
and then say, "Find out on the show."

1831
01:08:40,576 --> 01:08:42,351
[Absolutely loves it]
Ah, I like that.

1832
01:08:42,351 --> 01:08:44,444
Why is your brain working so well, Seo Jun?

1833
01:08:44,444 --> 01:08:46,811
[All that's left is evening tickets to Gimpo]
Then let me check round-trip tickets first.

1834
01:08:46,811 --> 01:08:49,673
And then, we go from Gimpo to Egg ** Coming.

1835
01:08:49,673 --> 01:08:51,500
[Searching]

1836
01:08:51,500 --> 01:08:53,008
Darn it...

1837
01:08:53,008 --> 01:08:54,554
- Hey, what's wrong with this?
- Why is it like this?

1838
01:08:54,554 --> 01:08:56,358
[All tickets are over 100,000 won per person]
Scroll down, scroll down.

1839
01:08:56,358 --> 01:08:57,828
I don't think we can come back.

1840
01:08:57,828 --> 01:08:59,782
[Plan B in danger]
Just on the 2nd...

1841
01:08:59,782 --> 01:09:03,679
Wait, then let's just change
the date to the 2nd. Right?

1842
01:09:03,679 --> 01:09:05,382
- I don't think we can come back.
- Wait, on the 2nd...

1843
01:09:05,382 --> 01:09:08,530
- Why is it so expensive?
- It's 120,000 won...

1844
01:09:09,271 --> 01:09:11,673
[1st: 139k, 2nd: 120k,
3rd: 111k, 4th: 25k, 5th: 15k]

1845
01:09:11,673 --> 01:09:14,506
- 110,000 won?
- Should we just stay until the 5th?

1846
01:09:14,506 --> 01:09:16,116
[Plan C, Extend filming by 4 days]

1847
01:09:16,116 --> 01:09:17,506
Why is this happening?

1848
01:09:17,506 --> 01:09:22,097
Ah, I can't stay until the 5th either.
I already have plans too.

1849
01:09:22,097 --> 01:09:25,130
- I have to go to Japan on the 6th.
- You're going to Japan?

1850
01:09:25,130 --> 01:09:26,431
[An unbelievably harsh reality...]
Wait, this...

1851
01:09:26,431 --> 01:09:28,457
- Why is this like this?
- Why is this like this?

1852
01:09:28,457 --> 01:09:31,659
- Wait a second.
- Ah! No, wait. It's because...

1853
01:09:31,659 --> 01:09:33,782
it's because we searched Jeju to Gimpo.

1854
01:09:33,782 --> 01:09:36,632
Then where do we go?
Where were you trying to go then?

1855
01:09:36,632 --> 01:09:39,138
Let's go from Jeju to Busan.

1856
01:09:41,028 --> 01:09:43,463
[Plan D, Jeju to Busan]
- Busan's similar too. - Probably the same.

1857
01:09:43,463 --> 01:09:44,539
It's similar.

1858
01:09:44,539 --> 01:09:47,107
[Lowest fare, 71,500 won per person]
- 70,000 won. - It's 70,000 won.

1859
01:09:47,107 --> 01:09:48,710
Still can't come back.

1860
01:09:48,710 --> 01:09:50,639
[With Busan added, they go over budget]
And...

1861
01:09:50,639 --> 01:09:53,363
- Ah...
- Still can't come back.

1862
01:09:55,402 --> 01:09:58,775
- We should've gone to Jeju from the start.
- Right?

1863
01:09:58,775 --> 01:10:01,935
Ah, we really can't make it to Jeju after all?

1864
01:10:03,179 --> 01:10:04,617
I want to go...

1865
01:10:04,617 --> 01:10:08,739
- I want to go even if it's just a day trip.
- I want to turn back time right now.

1866
01:10:08,739 --> 01:10:11,105
Just give up on Jeju.

1867
01:10:11,105 --> 01:10:13,205
We can't come back.

1868
01:10:13,205 --> 01:10:15,398
We can't afford to go.

1869
01:10:15,398 --> 01:10:17,255
We can't come back.

1870
01:10:17,255 --> 01:10:20,888
But, honestly... seriously...

1871
01:10:20,888 --> 01:10:23,834
if we really want to go,
we can just take a ferry.

1872
01:10:23,834 --> 01:10:26,619
[Plan E, Go to Jeju by ferry]
- Should we look up ferries? - Huh? Ferries?

1873
01:10:26,619 --> 01:10:28,274
Chat**T.

1874
01:10:28,274 --> 01:10:31,154
[Searching for ferries to Jeju using AI]

1875
01:10:31,154 --> 01:10:34,632
I'm in Gwangju right now.

1876
01:10:34,632 --> 01:10:37,678
I really want to go to Jeju, you know.

1877
01:10:38,326 --> 01:10:40,843
But I have to go by ferry...

1878
01:10:40,843 --> 01:10:42,998
This is my first time using this on a PC.

1879
01:10:42,998 --> 01:10:45,747
The money we have is...

1880
01:10:45,747 --> 01:10:47,451
Is it about 250,000 won?

1881
01:10:47,451 --> 01:10:51,467
- Just put in 250,000 won for now.
- It's 250,000 won.

1882
01:10:52,473 --> 01:10:55,200
"Tell me what options are available
starting tomorrow morning."

1883
01:10:55,200 --> 01:10:57,293
Starting in the morning...

1884
01:10:57,293 --> 01:10:59,593
From now on,

1885
01:10:59,593 --> 01:11:02,818
you are a travel guide.

1886
01:11:02,818 --> 01:11:06,010
[The question has been asked]

1887
01:11:06,010 --> 01:11:08,014
[What will the AI's answer be?]
Let's do this.

1888
01:11:08,014 --> 01:11:10,065
Let's go!

1889
01:11:10,766 --> 01:11:12,703
Let's go!

1890
01:11:12,703 --> 01:11:15,057
Alright, let's see...

1891
01:11:16,565 --> 01:11:18,295
Mokpo, Wando, Yeosu...

1892
01:11:19,848 --> 01:11:23,171
[He asked for ferries, and it suddenly
started talking about flights]

1893
01:11:23,171 --> 01:11:26,172
I definitely...

1894
01:11:26,172 --> 01:11:29,807
said ferry, didn't I?

1895
01:11:29,807 --> 01:11:31,734
[Woo Shik boldly putting AI in its place]

1896
01:11:33,627 --> 01:11:36,318
[The AI refuses to lose confidence]
Alright.

1897
01:11:36,318 --> 01:11:40,989
[Recommended: Nokdong, Mokpo, or Wando to Jeju]
- Nokdong Port? - Mokpo Port, Wando Port...

1898
01:11:40,989 --> 01:11:43,844
Hey Chat**T, are you seriously
going to keep doing this?

1899
01:11:43,844 --> 01:11:46,789
That almost became a disaster, seriously...

1900
01:11:46,789 --> 01:11:50,042
- But Chat**T gets things wrong a lot too.
- Yeah.

1901
01:11:50,042 --> 01:11:51,488
Select travel.

1902
01:11:51,488 --> 01:11:54,135
[Official site fact-check is essential]
- From Nokdong New Port to Jeju Port... - Yes.

1903
01:11:54,135 --> 01:11:56,471
- Is the date tomorrow?
- The 28th.

1904
01:11:56,471 --> 01:11:58,755
- Nothing.
- There's nothing.

1905
01:11:58,755 --> 01:12:00,769
[Nokdong New Port OUT]

1906
01:12:00,769 --> 01:12:02,350
Nothing...

1907
01:12:02,350 --> 01:12:05,447
- Check the next day. The 1st.
- There's nothing.

1908
01:12:05,447 --> 01:12:08,367
- What about the 2nd?
- There is one on the 2nd. The 2nd.

1909
01:12:09,133 --> 01:12:10,205
Awesome!

1910
01:12:10,205 --> 01:12:11,706
Hey!

1911
01:12:12,711 --> 01:12:16,265
I just checked, and there aren't any ferries!

1912
01:12:16,992 --> 01:12:18,593
Why isn't it showing up?

1913
01:12:18,593 --> 01:12:20,161
[Why isn't it showing up?
Ferries run depending on season and demand]

1914
01:12:20,161 --> 01:12:22,926
[Quite a shameless AI]

1915
01:12:22,926 --> 01:12:24,401
You're...

1916
01:12:24,401 --> 01:12:26,985
disqualified as a guide.

1917
01:12:27,839 --> 01:12:31,072
[Fair enough, I really messed up this time]
"Fair enough?"

1918
01:12:31,072 --> 01:12:33,812
Ah, I'm so annoyed!

1919
01:12:33,812 --> 01:12:36,083
Hey, Chat**T, are you seriously
gonna keep doing this?

1920
01:12:36,083 --> 01:12:38,891
Do it again. Mokpo Port to Jeju Port.

1921
01:12:38,891 --> 01:12:40,657
Huh? There is one.

1922
01:12:40,657 --> 01:12:42,050
Wait a second, Mokpo Port...

1923
01:12:42,050 --> 01:12:44,508
- Mokpo Port?
- Search Mokpo Port.

1924
01:12:45,636 --> 01:12:47,446
Ahh! Darn it!

1925
01:12:47,446 --> 01:12:50,225
[Will there be a ferry from Mokpo Port?]
Shoot!

1926
01:12:50,225 --> 01:12:52,058
Next one, shoot!

1927
01:12:52,058 --> 01:12:54,903
- Huh? Detailed search.
- 1 AM...

1928
01:12:54,903 --> 01:12:58,120
[Departs at a shocking 1 AM]

1929
01:13:00,028 --> 01:13:03,939
- What is this?
- Then we have to go later tonight.

1930
01:13:03,939 --> 01:13:07,492
We have to go later...
we have to eat first and then go.

1931
01:13:08,183 --> 01:13:09,692
Is it 1 PM?

1932
01:13:09,692 --> 01:13:11,432
[Trying to deny the harsh reality]
- Huh? No, we have to go later. - 1 AM...

1933
01:13:11,432 --> 01:13:13,432
- Tonight...
- It's 1 AM.

1934
01:13:13,432 --> 01:13:14,758
[K.O.]

1935
01:13:14,758 --> 01:13:16,017
Scroll down first.

1936
01:13:16,017 --> 01:13:18,585
[At least trying to check the price...]
Today... hey, this is way too expensive.

1937
01:13:18,585 --> 01:13:19,979
[Lowest fare: 35,400 won per person!]
Hey, it's 1 AM.

1938
01:13:19,979 --> 01:13:21,346
- Oh, 30,000...
- It's 35,000 won.

1939
01:13:21,346 --> 01:13:25,312
- We can just take economy seats.
- Woo Shik, no, wait...

1940
01:13:25,312 --> 01:13:27,179
Hey guys, should we eat first and then go?

1941
01:13:27,179 --> 01:13:30,512
- That is nice though.
- Ah, I feel like throwing up.

1942
01:13:31,239 --> 01:13:34,068
- But I'm curious about something.
- Yeah.

1943
01:13:34,068 --> 01:13:36,748
[The realist has come back to their senses]
- Do we really have to go this far? - For Jeju?

1944
01:13:36,748 --> 01:13:39,847
Ah, now that we suddenly can't go to Jeju,
I want to go even more.

1945
01:13:39,847 --> 01:13:42,567
Well, that's true, but...

1946
01:13:43,465 --> 01:13:45,247
Okay. Then...

1947
01:13:45,247 --> 01:13:49,300
[Even the dreamer Woo Shik starts giving up]
- I think we really did our best. - Yeah?

1948
01:13:49,300 --> 01:13:51,315
- It's really disappointing though, right?
- Yeah.

1949
01:13:51,315 --> 01:13:53,922
Ah, we should've gone on the first day.

1950
01:13:53,922 --> 01:13:56,728
Ah, if only we had gone on the first day...

1951
01:13:56,728 --> 01:13:58,416
We should've gone
on the first day and come back.

1952
01:13:58,416 --> 01:14:00,768
[All Jeju plans FAILED]

1953
01:14:00,768 --> 01:14:02,894
So, going for Hanwoo *** is confirmed now?

1954
01:14:02,894 --> 01:14:05,181
Ah, I'm so hungry.

1955
01:14:05,181 --> 01:14:06,987
Let's go to Hanwoo ***.

1956
01:14:06,987 --> 01:14:10,906
But the passion for Jeju was real.

1957
01:14:10,906 --> 01:14:13,608
[From 4:30 to 6:00, a full hour and a half...]

1958
01:14:13,608 --> 01:14:15,011
[The Jeju debate finally ends]

1959
01:14:15,011 --> 01:14:16,464
Ah, I'm hungry.

1960
01:14:16,464 --> 01:14:19,641
[However...]

1961
01:14:19,641 --> 01:14:23,954
[Another port they missed out on...]

1962
01:14:23,954 --> 01:14:25,086
[Next week]

1963
01:14:25,086 --> 01:14:27,389
If we all feel the same way,

1964
01:14:27,389 --> 01:14:29,926
I'm willing to challenge it anytime.

1965
01:14:29,926 --> 01:14:32,042
[An undying passion for Jeju]
We're going. Let's go first.

1966
01:14:32,042 --> 01:14:33,728
We're definitely going to Jeju.

1967
01:14:33,728 --> 01:14:35,258
[Eventually, late at night...]
But first, we need to see if there are tickets.

1968
01:14:35,258 --> 01:14:37,113
[The second debate breaks out]
Let's think realistically.

1969
01:14:37,113 --> 01:14:39,020
If we get to Jeju, how are we getting back out?

1970
01:14:39,020 --> 01:14:40,581
We can't afford the flights.

1971
01:14:40,581 --> 01:14:42,553
The travel time alone is seriously insane.

1972
01:14:42,553 --> 01:14:44,239
[After endless discussion]

1973
01:14:44,239 --> 01:14:46,306
[What method did they choose?]
I think it could totally work.

1974
01:14:46,306 --> 01:14:48,699
Ah! This is driving me crazy.

1975
01:14:48,699 --> 01:14:50,545
- I'm so nervous.
- Ah, but I feel like it's gonna happen.

1976
01:14:50,545 --> 01:14:52,147
[The final benefit draw]
Don't hesitate, just go right in.

1977
01:14:52,147 --> 01:14:54,950
[Today's fate is in Seo Jun's hands]
- Go right in. - Probably the last draw.

1978
01:14:54,950 --> 01:14:56,606
[What are they hoping for?]
- Did you pull it? - Yeah, he pulled it.

1979
01:14:56,606 --> 01:14:58,888
Ah, but we really need a car in Jeju.

1980
01:14:58,888 --> 01:15:00,902
[Please give us a car]
Please! Please!

1981
01:15:00,902 --> 01:15:03,027
- Should I open it all at once?
- Just a little, just a little.

1982
01:15:03,027 --> 01:15:05,262
- Okay, huh?
- Huh? Wait a second.

1983
01:15:05,262 --> 01:15:08,104
[Did they get the car they wanted?]

1984
01:15:08,104 --> 01:15:09,159
[The trio finally heads to Jeju]
Let's enjoy this moment.

1985
01:15:09,159 --> 01:15:10,545
Wow, we're actually going to Jeju?

1986
01:15:10,545 --> 01:15:12,891
- Are we having black pork for dinner?
- Let's go!

1987
01:15:12,891 --> 01:15:15,579
[Now they just need to buy the boarding passes]
The 14:30 flight to Jeju...

1988
01:15:15,579 --> 01:15:16,779
Yes, the cheapest one please.

1989
01:15:16,779 --> 01:15:18,206
Wasn't it 32,000 won?

1990
01:15:18,206 --> 01:15:20,791
178,910 won one way.

1991
01:15:20,791 --> 01:15:22,700
178,910 won one way?

1992
01:15:22,700 --> 01:15:24,378
[The crisis continues until the very end]

1993
01:15:24,378 --> 01:15:25,588
Yes.

1994
01:15:25,588 --> 01:15:28,130
- How much do we have left?
- There's barely anything left, huh?

1995
01:15:28,130 --> 01:15:31,519
- But first, even the meat costs...
- I don't think we can even eat meat.

1996
01:15:31,519 --> 01:15:35,924
But the whole reason
we wanted to go to Jeju was to eat good food.

1997
01:15:35,924 --> 01:15:37,107
Then should we just sleep at the port?

1998
01:15:37,107 --> 01:15:38,314
[Trying to go to Jeju and ending up homeless]

1999
01:15:38,314 --> 01:15:39,408
Then wait a second.

2000
01:15:39,408 --> 01:15:42,930
We're slowly losing
the whole point of going to Jeju...

2001
01:15:42,930 --> 01:15:43,990
This is getting interesting.

2002
01:15:43,990 --> 01:15:47,294
- Yeah. Woo Shik, you like tough stuff, right?
- Yeah.

2003
01:15:47,294 --> 01:15:50,191
Oh, but I need a cup of coffee right now.
I'm too tired.

2004
01:15:50,191 --> 01:15:53,265
Let's just grab a cup of coffee.
What do you think?

2005
01:15:56,552 --> 01:15:58,376
- No one's answering.
- They're too quiet...
